3
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:08,194
[GASPS]

4
00:02:31,351 --> 00:02:33,219
[MOANING]

5
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:45,331
[GRUNTING]

6
00:02:46,799 --> 00:02:48,601
[GASPS]

7
00:02:48,635 --> 00:02:51,371
BABY, IT'S OKAY,
YOU'RE DREAMING.

8
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,595
[TV CLICKING ON]

9
00:03:15,628 --> 00:03:17,497
[MAN CHATTERING ON TV]

10
00:03:19,432 --> 00:03:21,935
COME ON, SWEETHEART,
WE'VE GOTTA GO.
I'M GONNA MISS MY FLIGHT.

11
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:25,371
OKAY. YOU SEEM TENSE.
YOU DIDN'T HAVE
THAT DREAM AGAIN, DID YOU?

12
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:26,806
NO.

13
00:03:28,408 --> 00:03:30,944
I'M JUST ANXIOUS
ABOUT THE MEETING.

14
00:03:30,977 --> 00:03:33,446
I'VE GOTTA
MAKE THIS GUY TALK,

15
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:36,749
OR ELSE MY STORY SUCKS,
GRIFF WILL NEVER BUY IT,
AND THERE GOES MY INTERNSHIP.

16
00:03:36,783 --> 00:03:38,985
JUST BE FIRM.
DON'T LET HIM INTIMIDATE YOU.

17
00:03:39,018 --> 00:03:41,454
IT'S EASIER SAID THAN DONE.
THE GUY'S TOUGH.

18
00:03:41,487 --> 00:03:44,023
YOU KNOW INTIMIDATION
IS NOT EXACTLY MY STRONG SUIT.

19
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:47,994
HEY, YOU'RE SMART, KIDDO.
I KNOW YOU CAN DO IT.

20
00:03:49,963 --> 00:03:51,631
COME ON.
ALL RIGHT.

21
00:03:59,672 --> 00:04:02,575
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
THE WHITE ZONE IS
FOR IMMEDIATE LOADING...

22
00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:05,678
ALL RIGHT, REMEMBER,
NERVES OF STEEL.

23
00:04:05,712 --> 00:04:07,847
I'LL TRY.
DON'T TRY, JUST DO IT.

24
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:12,485
BE A GOOD GIRL, HONEY.

25
00:04:14,387 --> 00:04:15,989
I'M ALWAYS GOOD.

26
00:04:20,059 --> 00:04:21,694
[MOUTHING WORDS]

27
00:04:21,728 --> 00:04:24,497
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER]
THE WHITE ZONE IS
FOR IMMEDIATE LOADING

28
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:26,933
AND UNLOADING
OF PASSENGERS ONLY.

29
00:04:26,966 --> 00:04:28,835
NO PARKING.

30
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:34,707
[BLOWING WHISTLE]

31
00:04:34,741 --> 00:04:36,743
I'M GOING, I'M GOING.

32
00:04:40,413 --> 00:04:42,682
[PASSENGERS CHATTERING]

33
00:04:47,987 --> 00:04:50,456
[WOMAN OVER P.A.]
WE'RE PROCEEDING
TO TAXI ONTO THE RUNWAY.

34
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:54,761
AT THIS TIME WE ASK
TO YOU FASTEN YOUR SEATBELTS
AND PREPARE FOR TAKEOFF.

35
00:04:54,794 --> 00:04:56,496
[SIGHS]

36
00:05:05,838 --> 00:05:08,408
HI.
HELLO. HOW ARE YOU?

37
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:10,043
OH, I'M FINE.

38
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:12,679
LOOKS LIKE IT'S
GONNA BE A SHORT FLIGHT.

39
00:05:12,712 --> 00:05:15,448
NOT SHORT ENOUGH
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED.

40
00:05:15,481 --> 00:05:17,083
THEY NEVER GIVE US
ENOUGH LEG SPACE.

41
00:05:17,116 --> 00:05:18,518
[CHUCKLES]

42
00:05:18,551 --> 00:05:20,520
YOU'RE RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

43
00:05:20,553 --> 00:05:22,488
[WOMAN]
SO, WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO SAN FRANCISCO?

44
00:05:22,522 --> 00:05:25,458
A STORY ON A CITY BIG-WIG
WHO'S BEEN IMPLICATED
IN A HUGE SEX SCANDAL.

45
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:27,460
HOW EXCITING.
WHO DO YOU WRITE FOR?

46
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,028
WE@R
 MAGAZINE.

47
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:33,166
GREAT ARTICLES.
YOU LIVE IN L.A.?
YEAH. DO YOU?

48
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:35,435
I NOW SPEND MOST
OF MY TIME UP NORTH.

49
00:05:35,468 --> 00:05:37,637
WE HAVE A HOME
IN NAPA VALLEY.
MMM.

50
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:39,439
I LOVE THE WEATHER.

51
00:05:39,472 --> 00:05:42,709
I HAVE SPACE TO THINK,
RIDE MY HORSES.

52
00:05:42,742 --> 00:05:44,711
IT'S SO HARD
TO FOCUS IN L.A.

53
00:05:44,744 --> 00:05:48,948
MY HUSBAND, THOUGH, HE PREFERS
THE HOUSE BY THE BEACH.

54
00:05:48,981 --> 00:05:51,184
GOD, IT MUST BE BEAUTIFUL
UP THERE RIGHT NOW.

55
00:05:51,217 --> 00:05:53,586
STORYBOOK GREEN, RIGHT?

56
00:05:53,619 --> 00:05:55,955
I WENT TO CATHOLIC
BOARDING SCHOOL UP THERE.

57
00:05:55,988 --> 00:05:58,658
NOTHING BUT GREEN PASTURES
AND COWS.

58
00:05:58,691 --> 00:06:03,496
OH, WE REPLACED THE MILK
WITH THE WINE, DARLING,
A LONG TIME AGO.

59
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:06,199
HOW FUNNY. I WENT TO CATHOLIC
BOARDING SCHOOL MYSELF.

60
00:06:06,232 --> 00:06:07,900
YOU DIDN'T.

61
00:06:09,902 --> 00:06:11,838
YOU KNOW, MY HUSBAND
ALWAYS TEASES ME.

62
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:15,475
HE SAYS THAT THAT'S WHY
I'M SO SCREWED UP--
FOUR YEARS WITHOUT BOYS.

63
00:06:15,508 --> 00:06:17,477
MY HUSBAND WOULD AGREE.

64
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:20,680
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?
THEY'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.
PROBABLY RIGHT.

65
00:06:27,086 --> 00:06:29,055
[ELIZABETH]
YOUR ELECTRONIC PARKING CARD

66
00:06:29,088 --> 00:06:32,024
SHOWS YOU DIDN'T
CHECK OUT OF THE GARAGE
UNTIL MIDNIGHT THAT NIGHT.

67
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:33,593
[MAN]
SOMETIMES I WORK LATE.

68
00:06:33,626 --> 00:06:37,196
[ELIZABETH] CAN YOU TELL ME
WHY BEVERLY WAS AT YOUR OFFICE
THE NIGHT OF THE RAPE?

69
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,698
SHE WASN'T AT MY OFFICE.

70
00:06:38,731 --> 00:06:41,033
I SAW HER WAITING
AT THE BUS STOP
OUT OF MY WINDOW.

71
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:43,202
THAT WAS NEVER
IN THE POLICE REPORT.

72
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:46,239
THERE WAS NEVER A BUS SCHEDULED
FOR THAT LINE, THAT NIGHT.

73
00:06:46,272 --> 00:06:49,575
HOW COULD SHE HAVE BEEN
WAITING FOR A BUS THAT
WAS NEVER SCHEDULED?

74
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:51,778
I'M GONNA TRY TO SAY THIS
IN A NICE WAY

75
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:55,181
ABOUT SOMETHING THAT
COULD GET EXTREMELY UGLY.

76
00:06:55,214 --> 00:06:58,818
IT WOULD BE VERY WISE
OF YOU NOT TO PROCEED
WITH YOUR INQUIRIES.

77
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:04,590
GOOD, WE AGREE.
THERE IS NO STORY.

78
00:07:04,624 --> 00:07:06,893
YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,
MISS BARTON.

79
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:10,963
[SIGHS]

80
00:07:15,701 --> 00:07:17,036
TAXI!

81
00:07:35,688 --> 00:07:38,558
I HAVE A RESERVATION
FOR MRS. BARTON, PLEASE.

82
00:07:40,993 --> 00:07:42,195
ELIZABETH?

83
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:44,564
OH, MY GOD,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

84
00:07:44,597 --> 00:07:48,301
MY FLIGHT WAS CANCELLED--
THE FOG.
MINE TOO. ISN'T THIS CRAZY?

85
00:07:48,334 --> 00:07:52,638
BOB, THIS IS THE WOMAN
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.
WE MET ON THE WAY UP.

86
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:53,573
PLEASURE.

87
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:56,108
NICE TO MEET YOU.
JOIN US FOR A NIGHTCAP?

88
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:01,147
OH, COME ON,
LIVE A LITTLE DANGEROUSLY.
IT'LL BE FUN.

89
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,718
WHY NOT?

90
00:08:10,022 --> 00:08:11,557
EXCUSE ME.

91
00:08:15,261 --> 00:08:18,598
I DIDN'T REALIZE YOUR HUSBAND
WAS JOINING YOU UP HERE.

92
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:21,701
BOB? OH, HE'S NOT MY HUSBAND.

93
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:26,305
OH, COME ON, DARLING,
DON'T SAY YOU DIDN'T
FIGURE IT OUT.

94
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,074
WRITERS ALWAYS FIGURE IT OUT.

95
00:08:28,107 --> 00:08:30,209
WOULDN'T YOU SAY, BOB?

96
00:08:30,243 --> 00:08:31,944
YOU'RE INTERESTED
IN CHARACTER, AREN'T YOU?

97
00:08:31,978 --> 00:08:36,349
OH, YEAH. AND I'M
INTERESTED IN DESSERT.

98
00:08:36,382 --> 00:08:39,719
REAL DECADENT
AND SWEET.

99
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:54,700
[WOMAN LAUGHING]

100
00:08:56,235 --> 00:08:58,838
SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
DO TO ME TONIGHT?

101
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:02,675
THAT'S KIND OF A STRANGE
QUESTION, 'CAUSE WHEN YOU
SEE IT, YOU WON'T BELIEVE IT.

102
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:04,710
[LAUGHING]

103
00:09:04,744 --> 00:09:08,614
GOOD NIGHT. I'LL CALL
YOU BACK IN L.A.
OKAY. GOOD NIGHT.

104
00:09:08,648 --> 00:09:11,284
GOOD NIGHT.
[CHUCKLES]

105
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:19,759
WHY DON'T YOU START
SHOWING ME?

106
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:35,741
[SOFTLY MOANING]

107
00:09:47,386 --> 00:09:49,388
[TROLLEY BELL RINGING]

108
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,964
[BOB'S VOICE MURMURING]

109
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:16,816
[BOB, WOMAN SOFTLY MOANING]

110
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:27,827
[MOANING CONTINUES]

111
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:53,686
[MOANING]

112
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:20,980
[MAN] SO WHAT
YOU'RE SAYING IS A YEAR AGO,
WE WOULD HAVE QUALIFIED.

113
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:25,284
I'M AFRAID WITH THE CHANGE
IN YOUR WIFE'S SALARY,

114
00:11:25,317 --> 00:11:27,720
IT MAKES IT RATHER IMPOSSIBLE
AT THIS TIME.

115
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:32,925
DUE TO THE CHANGE
IN YOUR WIFE'S SALARY.

116
00:11:32,958 --> 00:11:35,294
YOU CALL WHAT
THEY PAY A SALARY?

117
00:11:35,327 --> 00:11:36,429
HONEY, INTERNS DON'T--

118
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:37,463
YEAH, BUT CHRIST!

119
00:11:37,496 --> 00:11:41,133
75K A YEAR PLACING EXECUTIVES,
YOU HAD IT MADE.

120
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:44,203
NEVER HAVING TO LEAVE
THE HOUSE, NEVER HAVING
TO LEAVE YOUR STUDY.

121
00:11:44,236 --> 00:11:47,907
COME ON, HONEY. WE BOTH
KNEW IT WAS GONNA BE TOUGH
IN THE BEGINNING.

122
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:49,875
RECRUITING MADE ME MISERABLE.

123
00:11:49,909 --> 00:11:52,311
YOU DON'T WANT ME TO BE
MISERABLE, DO YOU?

124
00:11:52,344 --> 00:11:54,213
YEAH, BUT IT'S BEEN
OVER A YEAR NOW.

125
00:11:54,246 --> 00:11:57,083
I MEAN, WHY NOT AT LEAST
TRY ANOTHER PUBLICATION?

126
00:11:57,116 --> 00:11:59,952
WHAT'S SO BIG ABOUT
WE@R
 MAGAZINE, ANYWAY?

127
00:11:59,985 --> 00:12:03,089
GRIFFIN. HE'S THE BEST
EDITOR IN TOWN.
THAT'S RIGHT.

128
00:12:03,122 --> 00:12:06,992
YOUR MENTOR, THE ONE
WHO CHANGED YOUR LIFE
ONE COLLEGE AFTERNOON.

129
00:12:07,026 --> 00:12:09,395
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN
ONE HELL OF A LECTURE.

130
00:12:09,428 --> 00:12:11,363
ERIC, STOP IT!

131
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:15,801
LOOK, I'M PRETTY SURE HE'LL USE
THE PIECE I'M TURNING IN TODAY.

132
00:12:15,835 --> 00:12:20,840
THEN I'LL BE ON STAFF,
AND EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.
ALL RIGHT?

133
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:23,843
COME ON.

134
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:25,311
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

135
00:12:25,344 --> 00:12:27,146
GIVE ME A KISS.

136
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:36,055
[MAN]
WHY DO YOU
ALWAYS PRETEND, LAURA,

137
00:12:36,088 --> 00:12:39,458
THAT YOU DON'T HEAR
WHAT I SAY WHEN I KNOW
THAT YOU HEAR WHAT I SAY?

138
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:42,194
DO YOU WANT ME TO BELIEVE
THAT YOU'RE STUPID,
BECAUSE IF YOU DO,

139
00:12:42,228 --> 00:12:43,562
I WILL.

140
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:46,499
AND AS FOR YOU,
YOUNG LADY,

141
00:12:46,532 --> 00:12:47,867
THIS HAPPENS
TO BE A BUSINESS,

142
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:51,837
NOT A HOBBY BETWEEN
GETTING YOUR HAIR DONE
AND HAVING LUNCHES.

143
00:12:51,871 --> 00:12:54,073
YOUR STORY'S LATE.
WHERE IS IT?

144
00:12:55,074 --> 00:12:57,009
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

145
00:13:02,648 --> 00:13:04,483
ELIZABETH, THE FIRST LINE
DOESN'T WORK.

146
00:13:04,517 --> 00:13:07,186
THE STORY DOES.
I HOPE SO, FOR YOUR SAKE.

147
00:13:07,219 --> 00:13:10,556
STAFF MEETING TOMORROW
MORNING, 10 A.M. SHARP.
TRY TO BE THERE.

148
00:13:48,427 --> 00:13:50,296
♪ COME ON IN

149
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:54,266
♪ I'LL BE THERE IF I CAN

150
00:13:54,300 --> 00:14:00,906
♪ ANY TIME DAY OR NIGHT

151
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:03,609
♪ I KNOW THAT EVEN IF

152
00:14:03,642 --> 00:14:07,079
♪ I'M MILES FROM HOME

153
00:14:07,112 --> 00:14:10,282
♪ THE BRIDGES BREAK
THE TUNNELS BURN ♪

154
00:14:10,316 --> 00:14:14,019
COME ON, BABY. I'M READY.

155
00:14:14,053 --> 00:14:15,554
♪ THERE'S NOTHING ELSE
THAT'S COMING THROUGH ♪

156
00:14:15,588 --> 00:14:20,559
♪ SAID THERE'S NOTHING
IN THE WORLD THAT SHINES ♪

157
00:14:20,593 --> 00:14:22,328
♪ LIKE YOU

158
00:14:28,133 --> 00:14:30,002
♪ LIKE YOU

159
00:14:30,035 --> 00:14:32,137
[MAN]
OH, YEAH.
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

160
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:35,107
COME HERE.

161
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:36,408
MMM.

162
00:14:37,643 --> 00:14:40,145
[MOANING]

163
00:14:41,647 --> 00:14:45,517
YOU LIKE THAT? YEAH.

164
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:49,021
[MOANING]

165
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:06,105
OH, DOES THAT FEEL GOOD?

166
00:15:06,138 --> 00:15:09,675
YEAH.
[MOANING]

167
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:12,444
[BOTH MOANING]

168
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:25,190
HOW DID YOU KNOW HE'S
ONE OF MY FAVORITE ACTORS?

169
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:29,028
I THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE IT.

170
00:15:31,163 --> 00:15:34,099
WHERE DID YOU GET IT?
THE MASK.

171
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,101
IT'S A SECRET.

172
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:40,039
OH, YOU MEAN LIKE THE SECRET
OF WHO THE REAL BOB IS?

173
00:15:41,307 --> 00:15:43,075
DON'T WORRY, LOVELY.

174
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:46,178
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN YOUR CHECKERED PAST.

175
00:15:46,211 --> 00:15:48,514
I JUST WANNA KNOW
WHAT'S WHAT, WHO'S WHO.

176
00:15:48,547 --> 00:15:50,549
PURELY SOCIOLOGICAL.

177
00:15:50,582 --> 00:15:54,086
IF ANYTHING, IT GIVES
A CERTAIN EDGE TO THINGS.

178
00:15:58,691 --> 00:16:01,660
I LIKE AN EDGE.

179
00:16:03,228 --> 00:16:05,130
[MOANING]

180
00:16:13,238 --> 00:16:16,075
NOW, FOR OUR THEME ISSUE
ON SEXUAL IDENTITIES,

181
00:16:16,108 --> 00:16:21,213
JULIA'S GOING TO COVER
THE PIECE ON MARRIED MEN
AND THEIR INFIDELITIES.

182
00:16:21,246 --> 00:16:24,083
BE CAREFUL
WITH YOUR RESEARCH, JULIA.

183
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:25,751
[ALL LAUGHING]

184
00:16:25,784 --> 00:16:28,520
[GRIFF]
AND, CARL, YOU HAVE A HANDLE
ON THE GAY DATING SERVICE ISSUE?

185
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:30,556
I'M ALL OVER IT, GRIFF.

186
00:16:30,589 --> 00:16:32,458
I'LL COVER THE DEMOGRAPHICS.

187
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:35,227
GOOD.

188
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:38,564
THAT MAKES FOUR FEATURES.

189
00:16:38,597 --> 00:16:40,566
BUT I WANT TO HAVE A FIFTH.

190
00:16:40,599 --> 00:16:44,403
IF I DON'T HAVE AN ACCEPTABLE
IDEA BY NOON TOMORROW,

191
00:16:44,436 --> 00:16:48,440
I BELIEVE THERE MIGHT BE
A LITTLE TROUBLE IN PARADISE.

192
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:54,146
ELIZABETH, IN MY OFFICE.

193
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:04,356
YOU'VE GOT A PRETTY GOOD
STORY GOING THERE, BUT YOU
WIMPED OUT. HAVE A SEAT.

194
00:17:05,891 --> 00:17:09,128
I DISAGREE.
I THINK IT WORKS.
BULLSHIT.

195
00:17:10,362 --> 00:17:12,431
IT'S VERY OBVIOUS
THAT YOU BACKED OFF.

196
00:17:12,464 --> 00:17:14,233
ELIZABETH,
YOU SHOULD HAVE DUG IN,

197
00:17:14,266 --> 00:17:17,436
YOU SHOULD HAVE NAILED
THAT LAWYER MAN
RIGHT THERE AT THE END.

198
00:17:17,469 --> 00:17:21,273
YOU SHOULD HAVE
JUST CONFRONTED HIM
AND TAKEN HIM DOWN.

199
00:17:21,306 --> 00:17:22,741
NO GUTS, NO STORY.

200
00:17:24,176 --> 00:17:26,779
THE THING IS--
WHAT IS THE THING?

201
00:17:26,812 --> 00:17:29,681
[WOMAN OVER INTERCOM]
GRIFF, YOUR WIFE'S ON TWO.

202
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,183
I CAN'T TALK
TO HER RIGHT NOW.

203
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:35,287
WOULD YOU PLEASE TELL HER
I LOVE HER AND I'LL CALL
HER BACK IN A FEW MINUTES?

204
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:41,226
LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT THE THING ISN'T.

205
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:43,262
THE THING ISN'T JUNIOR LEAGUE.
THIS IS JOURNALISM.

206
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:46,365
AND JOURNALISM
IS TELLING THE TRUTH.
IF YOU CAN'T TELL THE TRUTH,

207
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,233
THEN WE DO HAVE A PROBLEM.

208
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:51,270
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO GET TOUGH, ELIZABETH.

209
00:17:51,303 --> 00:17:52,704
THE THING IS, I JUST--

210
00:17:52,738 --> 00:17:55,340
DON'T TELL ME
WHAT THE THING IS!

211
00:17:57,576 --> 00:18:00,679
WE ALL HAVE OUR DEMONS.
NOW, THE BOTTOM LINE IS,

212
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:03,415
IF YOU CAN'T CONFRONT
YOUR DEMONS
AND NAIL YOUR ENDINGS,

213
00:18:03,449 --> 00:18:08,554
WELL, THEN MAYBE
YOU JUST DON'T BELONG HERE.

214
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:11,657
WILL YOU PLEASE EXCUSE ME.
I'D LIKE TO CALL MY WIFE.

215
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:23,302
[ERIC]
MY SAUCE CAME OUT GREAT.

216
00:18:33,345 --> 00:18:35,314
