OKAY, BYE.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

436
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:17,208
[GAGGING]
GET THE TAPE.

437
00:31:17,242 --> 00:31:19,043
[ANN]
THE TAPE.

438
00:31:21,012 --> 00:31:22,513
[SIGHS]

439
00:31:45,103 --> 00:31:48,072
[WHISTLING]

440
00:32:00,051 --> 00:32:01,386
[ELIZABETH]
HER MESSAGE
SOUNDED FRANTIC,

441
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:04,322
BUT I COULDN'T QUITE
MAKE IT OUT.

442
00:32:04,355 --> 00:32:07,158
I THINK YOUR IMAGINATION'S
GETTING THE BEST OF YOU.

443
00:32:07,191 --> 00:32:09,727
LOOK, I JUST DON'T WANT
TO MISS HER CALL AGAIN.

444
00:32:09,761 --> 00:32:11,996
THERE IS SOMETHING DEFINITELY
OFF WITH THAT ANSWERING MACHINE.

445
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:15,500
YEAH, BUT STEVE AND MARY
ARE EXPECTING BOTH OF US.

446
00:32:15,533 --> 00:32:16,968
COME ON, HONEY.

447
00:32:18,703 --> 00:32:21,105
COME ON, A NIGHT OUT
WILL DO US GOOD.

448
00:32:21,139 --> 00:32:24,442
RELAX, UNWIND, A LITTLE WINE.

449
00:32:24,475 --> 00:32:29,414
I WANT TO, JUST NOT TONIGHT.
I HAVE TO STAY HERE.

450
00:32:31,816 --> 00:32:34,218
YOU ARE SO SELFISH,
YOU KNOW THAT?

451
00:32:34,252 --> 00:32:36,487
SPENDING YOUR DAYS
IN THERE STAGNATING.

452
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:40,491
I'M SICK OF THIS WRITING THING,
THIS-THIS FUCKING LITTLE HOBBY!

453
00:32:40,525 --> 00:32:42,694
YOU'RE MY WIFE!

454
00:32:53,604 --> 00:32:56,441
[CAR STARTING]

455
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:58,609
[CAR DRIVING AWAY]

456
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:09,654
[ANN]
IT'S SO RAW, SO PRIMAL.

457
00:33:09,687 --> 00:33:13,057
AND MY LOVER WANTS
THE SAME THING I DO--
FULFILLMENT.

458
00:33:13,091 --> 00:33:14,625
YOU SHOULD TRY IT.

459
00:33:14,659 --> 00:33:19,197
DARLING, THE ROMANCE FADES FROM
EVERYONE'S MARRIAGE EVENTUALLY.

460
00:33:24,802 --> 00:33:26,738
[METAL SCRAPING]

461
00:33:40,151 --> 00:33:42,286
DROPPED THE ANSWERING
MACHINE OFF.

462
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:45,656
THEY SAID IT'D BE
A COUPLE DAYS,
SO I GOT A REPLACEMENT.

463
00:33:45,690 --> 00:33:49,127
I TOOK THE TAPE OUT.
IT'S, UH, ON YOUR DESK.

464
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:51,195
ANY NEWS ABOUT ANN?

465
00:33:51,229 --> 00:33:53,865
NO.

466
00:33:53,898 --> 00:33:56,868
THERE'S SOMETHING REALLY WRONG
WITH HER NOT CALLING.

467
00:33:56,901 --> 00:33:58,536
THE NUMBER BEING DISCONNECTED.

468
00:33:58,569 --> 00:34:00,772
I CAN JUST FEEL IT.

469
00:34:00,805 --> 00:34:03,541
THE WOMAN CAME TO HER SENSES,
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

470
00:34:03,574 --> 00:34:07,412
I MEAN, WHY SHOULD SHE
EXPOSE HERSELF, HER AFFAIR?
SHE BAILED OUT.

471
00:34:07,445 --> 00:34:11,649
SHE WOULD TELL ME.
WE GOT CLOSE.

472
00:34:14,886 --> 00:34:16,754
PLEASE, YOU JUST MET.

473
00:34:16,788 --> 00:34:20,124
FACE IT, LIZZY,
SHE'S GONE,
SO IS YOUR STORY.

474
00:34:21,459 --> 00:34:25,329
NO!
IT'S NOT OVER!

475
00:34:26,564 --> 00:34:29,167
MAYBE IT'S A DIFFERENT STORY.

476
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:33,871
MAYBE IT'S A BIGGER STORY.
DON'T YOU GET IT, ERIC?

477
00:34:33,905 --> 00:34:36,474
I REALLY FEEL
LIKE THIS IS GONNA BE
MY BREAKTHROUGH PIECE.

478
00:34:36,507 --> 00:34:39,410
YOU KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
I'VE HEARD THAT PATHETIC LINE?

479
00:34:41,479 --> 00:34:43,648
[CRYING]

480
00:34:44,682 --> 00:34:46,717
LIZZY.

481
00:34:50,288 --> 00:34:51,656
JUST DROP
THIS WHOLE THING, HUH?

482
00:34:51,689 --> 00:34:54,725
COME ON, GIVE US A CHANCE
TO FINISH THE HOUSE,

483
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:56,761
BUILD A GREAT LIFE TOGETHER.

484
00:34:59,363 --> 00:35:02,333
FUCK YOU.
JESUS CHRIST.

485
00:35:02,366 --> 00:35:05,169
WHY SHOULD I GIVE UP
MY DREAMS LIKE YOU?

486
00:35:05,203 --> 00:35:10,475
JUST LET THEM SIT IN A CORNER
AND GATHER DUST LIKE
YOUR PHOTOGRAPHY EQUIPMENT?

487
00:35:10,508 --> 00:35:13,444
WHY IS THAT OKAY WITH YOU?

488
00:35:13,478 --> 00:35:15,213
IT'S NOT OKAY WITH ME.

489
00:35:15,246 --> 00:35:18,549
THERE'S JUST SO MUCH ABOUT US
THAT IS NOT OKAY.

490
00:35:18,583 --> 00:35:22,954
I KNOW DINNER
WAS CANCELED LAST NIGHT.

491
00:35:22,987 --> 00:35:25,189
WHERE WERE YOU?

492
00:35:27,458 --> 00:35:31,462
JUST HAVING A DRINK.
HAVING A COUPLE DRINKS.

493
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:34,532
BY MYSELF, ALONE. OKAY?

494
00:35:54,919 --> 00:35:57,755
[MACHINE BEEPS]

495
00:35:57,788 --> 00:35:59,490
[MAN]
ERIC, THIS IS DAVE
AT THE OFFICE.

496
00:35:59,524 --> 00:36:02,493
THE BOSS IS
[TAPE GURGLES] BIGALOW FILE
AND I CAN'T FIND IT.

497
00:36:02,527 --> 00:36:05,263
I KNOW YOU [TAPE GURGLES]
FOR SAFEKEEPING, YOU S.O.B.

498
00:36:05,296 --> 00:36:08,933
HE SEEMS PRETTY ANXIOUS,
SO CALL ME [TAPE GURGLES].

499
00:36:08,966 --> 00:36:10,968
[BEEPS]

500
00:36:11,002 --> 00:36:12,403
HEY, ELIZABETH, IT'S SARAH.

501
00:36:12,436 --> 00:36:17,475
WE HAVE [TAPE GURGLES] CALL
YOU. SO CALL ME WHEN YOU
GET A CHANCE. OKAY.

502
00:36:17,508 --> 00:36:19,343
[BEEPS]

503
00:36:19,377 --> 00:36:20,912
[ANN]
ELIZABETH,

504
00:36:20,945 --> 00:36:23,648
THOUGHT YOU MIGHT GET A KICK
OUT OF EAVESDROPPING
ON [TAPE GURGLES].

505
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:26,817
ALMOST LIKE BEING HERE.
HE'S SO GREAT.

506
00:36:28,286 --> 00:36:30,254
[TAPE FAST-FORWARDING]

507
00:36:30,288 --> 00:36:31,989
ANY TIME, DARLING.

508
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:36,427
[BOB]
TELL ME,
WHY [TAPE GURGLES]

509
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:38,296
[ANN GASPING]

510
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:41,399
[TAPE FAST-FORWARDING]

511
00:36:41,432 --> 00:36:43,467
[BOB MUTTERING,
TAPE GURGLES]

512
00:36:43,501 --> 00:36:46,671
[ANN SCREAMING]

513
00:36:48,940 --> 00:36:51,542
[BOB]
SO, LIKE, I'M IN THIS,
YOU KNOW, TOTAL FUNK.

514
00:36:51,576 --> 00:36:54,412
THE ACTING IS LIKE,
COMPLETELY BACK-BURNER.

515
00:36:54,445 --> 00:36:56,814
I'M LIKE BILL HOLDEN
IN "SUNSET BOULEVARD," RIGHT?

516
00:36:56,847 --> 00:37:01,419
AND I'M IN NEW YORK,
DOING MY USUAL SATURDAY
NIGHT AT THE PIERRE BAR.

517
00:37:01,452 --> 00:37:03,421
THE NIGHT MAN FLOATS ME
A DOUBLE CUANTRO,

518
00:37:03,454 --> 00:37:05,323
'CAUSE HE KNOWS I LIKE
THE FRENCH STUFF.

519
00:37:05,356 --> 00:37:07,925
IT IMPRESSES THE LADIES
OR WHATEVER.

520
00:37:07,959 --> 00:37:10,394
SAYS HE'S GOT A GUY
FROM L.A.,

521
00:37:10,428 --> 00:37:12,330
WANTS TO MEET ME,
IT'S A HUSH-HUSH THING.

522
00:37:12,363 --> 00:37:13,998
BUT HE SMELLS MONEY, RIGHT?

523
00:37:14,031 --> 00:37:16,667
SO RIGHT AWAY,
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,
I'M INTERESTED.

524
00:37:16,701 --> 00:37:18,936
ANYWAY, LISTEN TO THIS,
BY THE WAY.

525
00:37:18,970 --> 00:37:20,571
"BOB, THE NEWCOMER,

526
00:37:20,605 --> 00:37:23,541
"FROM NEW YORK,
WITH A HAUNTING PRESENCE,

527
00:37:23,574 --> 00:37:26,310
TURNS IN A TRULY
INSPIRING PERFORMANCE."
[LAUGHS]

528
00:37:26,344 --> 00:37:28,980
COOL!
ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?

529
00:37:29,013 --> 00:37:32,783
ANYWAY, SO, I MEET THE DUDE,
WHICH IS WHAT I CALL HIM,

530
00:37:32,817 --> 00:37:36,020
THE DUDE, RIGHT, AND HE
LAYS OUT THE GIG FOR ME.

531
00:37:36,053 --> 00:37:40,725
ALL I GOTTA DO, IS I HAVE
TO INITIATE AN AFFAIR
WITH THIS BROAD, RIGHT?

532
00:37:40,758 --> 00:37:43,594
BUT HE'S GONNA GIVE ME
ALL THE PARTICULARS THAT I NEED

533
00:37:43,628 --> 00:37:45,463
TO LIKE, PROPERLY SEDUCE HER.

534
00:37:45,496 --> 00:37:46,464
NO SHIT!
SERIOUSLY.

535
00:37:46,497 --> 00:37:48,432
I MEAN, HE'S GIVING ME
ALL THE ACCOUTREMENTS.

536
00:37:48,466 --> 00:37:51,035
I'M TALKING A CAR,
UPGRADING THREADS,
EVERYTHING, RIGHT?

537
00:37:51,068 --> 00:37:54,772
SO HE SHOWS ME A PICTURE.
I GOTTA SEE WHAT SHE LOOKS LIKE.

538
00:37:54,805 --> 00:37:57,475
AND SHE LOOKS GOOD.
I MEAN, SHE'S ALMOST A BABE.

539
00:37:57,508 --> 00:37:59,610
IT'S LIKE, I MEAN,
SHE'S A LITTLE BIT
SEDATE LOOKING.

540
00:37:59,644 --> 00:38:02,947
BUT I'M THINKING,
"THIS ISN'T A PROBLEM."
TOTALLY DOABLE, NAILABLE THING.

541
00:38:02,980 --> 00:38:05,383
PLUS, HE GOT YOU
THE LEAD IN THE PLAY, RIGHT?

542
00:38:05,416 --> 00:38:07,752
MM-HMM, YES.
GOD, I LOVE THIS CITY.

543
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:10,321
COCKROACH TO BUDDING STAR
IN TWO MONTHS.
MM-HMM.

544
00:38:19,964 --> 00:38:23,367
WHAT SORT OF EXTENSION
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT?
MAYBE JUST A WEEK.

545
00:38:23,401 --> 00:38:25,870
YOU'RE IN TROUBLE,
AREN'T YOU?

546
00:38:25,903 --> 00:38:27,438
NO.

547
00:38:27,471 --> 00:38:28,806
THEN LET'S HAVE IT.

548
00:38:28,839 --> 00:38:33,077
I JUST NEED A FEW DAYS
TO VERIFY SOME THINGS
THAT SHE TOLD ME.

549
00:38:33,110 --> 00:38:36,080
DON'T TRY TO BULLSHIT ME.
WHAT'S THE REAL REASON?

550
00:38:36,113 --> 00:38:38,849
I NEED TO NAIL MY ENDING.

551
00:38:38,883 --> 00:38:42,486
THAT'S ALL YOU HAD
TO SAY, ELIZABETH.

552
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:45,056
I'LL GIVE YOU ONE WEEK
BECAUSE I RESPECT YOUR HONESTY.

553
00:38:46,691 --> 00:38:51,062
ELIZABETH, WHICH ONE OF THESE
WOULD YOU GO WITH?

554
00:39:04,942 --> 00:39:06,610
WHO'S HE?

555
00:39:08,913 --> 00:39:10,748
THAT'S OUR CHOICE.

556
00:39:14,552 --> 00:39:18,122
[ELIZABETH]
SO, WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
YOU WERE AN ACTOR?

557
00:39:18,155 --> 00:39:22,560
UH, WELL, BECAUSE,
WHENEVER YOU SAY THAT,
PEOPLE THINK YOU'RE A FLAKE.

558
00:39:22,593 --> 00:39:24,095
ESPECIALLY IF
YOU'RE NOT FAMOUS.

559
00:39:24,128 --> 00:39:26,831
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

560
00:39:26,864 --> 00:39:30,768
WELL, I WAS INTERVIEWING ANN
FOR THIS STORY I'M DOING

561
00:39:30,801 --> 00:39:33,104
AND NOW SHE'S DISAPPEARED OFF
THE FACE OF THE EARTH.

562
00:39:33,137 --> 00:39:37,007
WHAT DOES THAT HAVE
TO DO WITH ME?

563
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:40,544
I MEAN, 'CAUSE IF YOU THINK
I CAN HOOK YOU UP WITH HER,
YOU'RE WRONG.

564
00:39:40,578 --> 00:39:42,580
ANYTHING PERSONAL
WOULD REALLY HELP.

565
00:39:42,613 --> 00:39:47,618
NO, SEE, ANN WAS-- SHE WAS
REAL GOOD AT KEEPING HER LIFE
EXTRA-PRIVATE.

566
00:39:47,651 --> 00:39:50,054
SO, ARE YOU SAYING THAT
YOU'RE HAVING A RELATIONSHIP

567
00:39:50,087 --> 00:39:53,524
WITH A WOMAN AND YOU DON'T KNOW
THE FIRST THING ABOUT HER?

568
00:39:53,557 --> 00:39:55,025
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

569
00:39:55,059 --> 00:39:57,595
NO, I'M NOT SAYING
THAT AT ALL. I KNOW PLENTY.

570
00:39:57,628 --> 00:39:59,897
I KNOW ALL KINDS OF THINGS.

571
00:39:59,930 --> 00:40:04,101
I KNOW, LIKE, UH,
WHAT HER FAVORITE FOREPLAY IS.

572
00:40:04,135 --> 00:40:06,737
I KNOW HOW SHE TREMBLES
JUST BEFORE SHE COMES.

573
00:40:06,771 --> 00:40:09,540
I KNOW LOTS OF THINGS
ABOUT HER, PRETTY PRIVATE STUFF,

574
00:40:09,573 --> 00:40:11,909
JUST NOT STUFF
THAT'S RIGHT FOR YOU
OR YOUR LITTLE INTERVIEW.

575
00:40:11,942 --> 00:40:14,945
HOW ABOUT HER HUSBAND?
DID SHE EVER MENTION HIM--
MAYBE WHERE HE WORKS,

576
00:40:14,979 --> 00:40:16,614
WHAT HE DOES FOR A LIVING?

577
00:40:16,647 --> 00:40:19,116
NOPE. WOULDN'T HAVE A CLUE.
I'M SURE SHE TOLD YOU.

578
00:40:19,150 --> 00:40:20,851
REALLY, IT WAS
NO STRINGS ATTACHED.

579
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:23,621
MAYBE SHE JUST HAD HER FILL
AND THOUGHT ENOUGH'S ENOUGH.

580
00:40:23,654 --> 00:40:27,591
HMM. LAST TIME
I SPOKE TO HER,

581
00:40:27,625 --> 00:40:29,727
SHE TOLD ME THAT SHE WAS
FALLING IN LOVE WITH YOU.

582
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,529
SHE SOUNDED VERY EXCITED.

583
00:40:31,562 --> 00:40:33,697
WHAT?
[LAUGHING]

584
00:40:33,731 --> 00:40:35,599
IT'S BULLSHIT.

585
00:40:35,633 --> 00:40:38,669
OKAY? SHE WAS IN LOVE
WITH HER HUSBAND, NOT ME.

586
00:40:38,702 --> 00:40:40,604
SHE HAD GREAT SEX WITH ME.

587
00:40:40,638 --> 00:40:42,740
IT WASN'T LOVE.

588
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:45,009
I THINK SHE KNOWS
THE DIFFERENCE.

589
00:40:45,042 --> 00:40:47,711
WELL, SHE'S WRONG.
SHE DIDN'T SOUND WRONG.

590
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:50,648
ANN CAN SOUND
A LOT OF WAYS, OKAY?

591
00:40:50,681 --> 00:40:52,650
SHE WAS VERY PRACTICED
IN THE ART OF DECEPTION.

592
00:40:52,683 --> 00:40:56,954
I HAVE A FEELING YOU'RE
NOT BAD AT IT YOURSELF.

593
00:40:56,987 --> 00:40:59,723
ONLY WHEN I'M PAID TO BE.

594
00:40:59,757 --> 00:41:01,559
I'M AN ACTOR.

595
00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:03,027
OH.

596
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:08,999
THAT'S NICE.
THANK YOU.

597
00:41:09,033 --> 00:41:12,636
SHE MADE QUITE A POINT
OF A CATHOLIC BOARDING SCHOOL
THAT SHE WENT TO.

598
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:14,572
GRADUATE AT THE
TOP OF HER CLASS.

599
00:41:14,605 --> 00:41:15,606
[LAUGHING]
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?

600
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:18,642
A CATHOLIC BOARDING SCHOOL,
THE TOP OF HER CLASS?

601
00:41:18,676 --> 00:41:21,946
COME ON. NO, NO, NO, NO.
ANN DIDN'T FINISH HIGH SCHOOL.

602
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:24,615
ARE YOU SURE?

603
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:26,550
I'M POSITIVE.

604
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:54,672
[ANSWERING MACHINE
MESSAGE, GARBLED]

605
00:43:05,082 --> 00:43:06,050
[TAPE REWINDING]

606
00:43:06,083 --> 00:43:09,019
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING TO SAY?
I FIGURED IT OUT.

607
00:43:09,053 --> 00:43:10,321
[GASPS]

608
00:43:10,354 --> 00:43:12,723
GOD, YOU SCARED
THE HELL OUT OF ME.

609
00:43:14,124 --> 00:43:15,426
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

610
00:43:15,459 --> 00:43:17,294
HOW DID YOU KNOW
WHERE I LIVE?

611
00:43:17,328 --> 00:43:19,430
WASN'T HARD TO FIND.

612
00:43:19,463 --> 00:43:24,435
WHAT DID YOU FIGURE OUT?
SOMETHING ABOUT ANN?

613
00:43:24,468 --> 00:43:27,705
NO.
ABOUT YOU.

614
00:43:29,873 --> 00:43:33,711
SEE, FIRST,
I THOUGHT TO MYSELF,

615
00:43:33,744 --> 00:43:37,348
WHAT IS THIS NICE,
HAPPILY MARRIED WOMAN DOING

616
00:43:37,381 --> 00:43:40,117
WRITING ABOUT
EXTRAMARITAL AFFAIRS?

617
00:43:40,150 --> 00:43:42,219
IT DOESN'T ADD UP.

618
00:43:42,252 --> 00:43:43,988
I GET PAID
TO BE INTERESTED.

619
00:43:44,021 --> 00:43:46,290
I DON'T BUY IT.

620
00:43:46,323 --> 00:43:48,859
THIS ISN'T ABOUT ANN
OR HER AFFAIRS.

621
00:43:48,892 --> 00:43:50,861
THIS IS ABOUT YOU.

622
00:43:50,894 --> 00:43:54,098
PORTRAIT OF THE WRITER
EMERGING FROM DARKNESS.
HMM?

623
00:43:55,799 --> 00:43:58,135
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.
IS IT?

624
00:43:58,168 --> 00:44:00,170
[CLEARS THROAT]
YOU'RE NOT LOOKING FOR ANN.

625
00:44:00,204 --> 00:44:01,972
YOU'RE TRYING
TO FIND YOURSELF.

626
00:44:02,006 --> 00:44:06,410
YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT ME.
YEAH? INDULGE ME.

627
00:44:06,443 --> 00:44:09,146
I MEAN, YOU--
YOU HAVE TAKEN GREAT CARE

628
00:44:09,179 --> 00:44:11,415
TO-TO HIDE YOUR LIFE

629
00:44:11,448 --> 00:44:14,818
INSIDE THIS NARROW
LITTLE COMFORT ZONE.

630
00:44:14,852 --> 00:44:19,723
IT IS SO OBVIOUS,
WHAT KIND OF WORLD
YOU'VE CREATED FOR YOURSELF.

631
00:44:19,757 --> 00:44:23,460
YOU ARE NOT THE SUCCESSFUL
WRITER THAT YOU SHOULD BE.
WHY IS THAT?

632
00:44:25,396 --> 00:44:28,866
BECAUSE TRYING
TO PROTECT OURSELVES
DOESN'T WORK-- IT NEVER DOES.

633
00:44:28,899 --> 00:44:32,870
LIFE IS NOT ABOUT
TRYING TO BE SAFE
AND COMFORTABLE.

634
00:44:32,903 --> 00:44:35,773
LIFE IS ABOUT ONE THING--
IT'S ABOUT LIVING.

635
00:44:35,806 --> 00:44:38,308
TO BE TRULY ALIVE,
ISN'T THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

636
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:40,911
TO FINALLY BE FREE?

637
00:44:42,913 --> 00:44:45,916
I UNDERSTAND THAT.
YOU SEE, I GET IT.

638
00:44:45,949 --> 00:44:48,819
I GET YOU.

639
00:44:48,852 --> 00:44:50,954
AND HE DOESN'T, DOES HE?

640
00:44:50,988 --> 00:44:53,957
YOUR HUSBAND, I MEAN.

641
00:44:53,991 --> 00:44:56,794
OF COURSE HE DOESN'T,
BECAUSE HE IS NOT LIKE US.

642
00:44:56,827 --> 00:45:00,130
HE'S NOT AN ARTIST.

643
00:45:00,164 --> 00:45:03,067
SOMETIMES I GET SO SCARED.

644
00:45:03,100 --> 00:45:04,802
I KNOW YOU DO.

645
00:45:04,835 --> 00:45:07,104
BUT IT'S CALLING YOU,

646
00:45:07,137 --> 00:45:09,206
AND YOU'VE GOT
TO FOLLOW YOUR HEART.

647
00:45:09,239 --> 00:45:13,410
BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
TO LIVE WITH REGRETS, DO YOU?

648
00:45:15,412 --> 00:45:17,214
HMM?

649
00:45:19,149 --> 00:45:21,418
NO.

650
00:45:21,452 --> 00:45:23,353
[PHONE RINGING]
[GASPS]

651
00:45:26,356 --> 00:45:28,425
HELLO?
[ERIC] I GOT
THE BIGALOW ACCOUNT!

652
00:45:28,459 --> 00:45:32,463
THAT'S GREAT, HONEY.
CAN YOU GIVE ME
A RIDE TO THE AIRPORT?

653
00:45:32,496 --> 00:45:37,067
SURE. JUST LET ME KNOW
WHERE AND WHEN. OKAY.
ALL RIGHT. I LOVE YOU.

654
00:45:42,239 --> 00:45:44,875
[SIGHS]

655
00:45:47,978 --> 00:45:52,149
[ANN'S VOICE, GARBLED]

656
00:45:56,987 --> 00:45:58,956
[BOB]
ARE YOU READY?

657
00:45:58,989 --> 00:46:02,326
[GARBLED TAPE CONTINUES]

658
00:46:12,136 --> 00:46:15,973
[ANN'S SCREAMS, GARBLED]

659
00:46:16,006 --> 00:46:20,978
SHE SOUNDED REALLY SCARED,
LIKE SOMETHING AWFUL
WAS ABOUT TO HAPPEN.

660
00:46:21,011 --> 00:46:23,547
ELIZABETH, STOP OBSESSING
ABOUT THIS, JUST DROP THE STORY.

661
00:46:23,580 --> 00:46:25,182
I CAN HANDLE IT!

662
00:46:25,215 --> 00:46:27,484
YOU KNOW, I DON'T
GET YOU ANYMORE.

663
00:46:27,518 --> 00:46:30,287
THIS SOUNDS DANGEROUS.
IT'S TIME TO BACK OFF, OKAY?

664
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:32,923
I CAN'T BACK OFF.
I HAVE TO DO THIS.

665
00:46:32,956 --> 00:46:36,226
I KNOW YOU PROBABLY
WOULDN'T UNDERSTAND. TRY ME.

666
00:46:36,260 --> 00:46:39,196
LIFE IS NOT ABOUT BEING SAFE,
IT'S NOT ABOUT PRETENDING.

667
00:46:39,229 --> 00:46:41,899
IT'S ABOUT SEEING THINGS
FOR WHAT THEY REALLY ARE.

668
00:46:41,932 --> 00:46:44,434
LIKE NOT PRETENDING
WE'RE NOT HAVING PROBLEMS
WITH OUR MARRIAGE,

669
00:46:44,468 --> 00:46:47,337
THAT I DIDN'T FIND
A BOOK IN THE CLOSET
FROM ANOTHER WOMAN,

670
00:46:47,371 --> 00:46:51,341
OBVIOUSLY A RELATIONSHIP
YOU FEEL YOU HAVE
TO HIDE FROM ME.

671
00:46:51,375 --> 00:46:53,977
WHY CAN'T YOU
LET GO OF THE PAST?

672
00:46:54,011 --> 00:46:58,315
WHY CAN'T YOU?
I CAN'T GET INTO THIS
RIGHT NOW. I GOTTA GO.

673
00:46:58,348 --> 00:47:01,985
YOU'VE ALWAYS GOTTA GO!
I'M NOT BACKING OFF, ERIC!

674
00:47:06,957 --> 00:47:10,060
[GRUNTING]
MAN, YOU ARE GOOD.

675
00:47:10,093 --> 00:47:13,297
IF I WERE GRIFF, I WOULD
NOT WANT TO MESS WITH YOU.

676
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:15,532
[PANTING]

677
00:47:15,566 --> 00:47:18,335
I THINK I FEEL BETTER.
YEAH.
[LAUGHING]

678
00:47:18,368 --> 00:47:21,438
IT'S YOUR TURN NOW. GREAT.

679
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:27,110
HEY, I'VE BEEN
MEANING TO ASK YOU,
HOW'D THAT SURPRISE GO?

680
00:47:27,144 --> 00:47:29,079
WHAT SURPRISE?

681
00:47:29,112 --> 00:47:32,216
YOU KNOW, ERIC SITTING
NEXT TO YOU ON THE FLIGHT
TO SAN FRANCISCO.

682
00:47:32,249 --> 00:47:34,151
I THOUGHT IT SOUNDED
VERY ROMANTIC.

683
00:47:34,184 --> 00:47:37,087
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT, LAURIE?

684
00:47:37,120 --> 00:47:38,956
WHAT?

685
00:47:38,989 --> 00:47:40,324
HIS SECRETARY CALLED ME

686
00:47:40,357 --> 00:47:43,060
AND SHE ASKED ME
TO BOOK A SEAT NEXT TO YOU.

687
00:47:43,093 --> 00:47:45,696
ERIC DOESN'T
HAVE A SECRETARY.

688
00:47:45,729 --> 00:47:47,364
HE DOESN'T?

689
00:47:48,398 --> 00:47:51,101
SO, WHO DID 
SIT NEXT TO YOU?

690
00:48:00,143 --> 00:48:02,579
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

691
00:48:02,613 --> 00:48:03,580
OKAY, I'M OUT OF HERE.

692
00:48:03,614 --> 00:48:06,216
HERE'S THE NUMBER
OF THE DETECTIVE IN NEW YORK.

693
00:48:06,250 --> 00:48:10,120
I GAVE HIM THE RUNDOWN
AND I TOLD HIM
TO CALL YOU WITH SOME ANSWERS.

694
00:48:10,153 --> 00:48:12,089
PERFECT. THANK YOU,
LAURIE. YOU'RE A LIFESAVER.

695
00:48:12,122 --> 00:48:15,225
I'M SO ON TOP OF IT,
IT'S SCARY.

696
00:48:15,259 --> 00:48:17,060
I'VE GOTTA RUN. CIAO.

697
00:48:17,094 --> 00:48:18,962
YOU HAVE A GOOD ONE.

698
00:48:20,464 --> 00:48:22,532
GOOD NIGHT, LAURIE.

699
00:48:23,533 --> 00:48:26,236
WELL, IT'S NICE
TO SEE YOU HERE.

700
00:48:26,270 --> 00:48:29,373
ONE MIGHT BELIEVE
YOU ARE ACTUALLY A WRITER.

701
00:48:29,406 --> 00:48:33,677
YEAH, LITTLE OLD ME,
OUT IN THE REAL WORLD
LIVING DANGEROUSLY.

702
00:48:33,710 --> 00:48:37,714
WHY THE LONG FACE?
YOU HAVING A LITTLE TROUBLE
WITH THE ARTICLE?

703
00:48:40,717 --> 00:48:43,353
WHY DON'T WE
GO ACROSS THE STREET

704
00:48:43,387 --> 00:48:46,356
AND HAVE OURSELVES A DRINK
AND WE CAN TALK ABOUT IT.

705
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:48,759
COME ON, GRIFF,
YOU KNOW I DON'T DRINK.

706
00:48:48,792 --> 00:48:51,495
YOU'RE A BIG GIRL, ELIZABETH.

707
00:48:51,528 --> 00:48:54,197
AND I'M A GOOD LISTENER.
COME ON.

708
00:48:57,034 --> 00:48:58,702
WHAT THE HELL.

709
00:49:05,175 --> 00:49:07,577
[ELIZABETH]
SHE'S IN THE SEAT NEXT TO ME,
SHE'S AT THE SAME HOTEL.

710
00:49:07,611 --> 00:49:11,348
MAKES SURE SHE RUNS INTO ME.
JUST TOO MANY COINCIDENCES.

711
00:49:11,381 --> 00:49:16,186
IT'S LIKE SHE'S LYING TO ME
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

712
00:49:16,219 --> 00:49:19,456
YOUR SUBJECT IS BECOMING
A SLIPPERY CHARACTER.

713
00:49:19,489 --> 00:49:21,625
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU HEARD FROM HER?

714
00:49:21,658 --> 00:49:23,493
FOUR DAYS AGO.

715
00:49:23,527 --> 00:49:25,529
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S REALLY WEIRD?

716
00:49:25,562 --> 00:49:29,299
I CAN'T QUITE EXPLAIN IT,
BUT IT'S LIKE SHE WANTS ME
TO WRITE THIS ARTICLE.

717
00:49:29,333 --> 00:49:32,336
LIKE SHE FOUND ME.

718
00:49:32,369 --> 00:49:35,672
I'D GIVE HER A COUPLE
OF DAYS. DO YOU HAVE
ANY LEADS TO GO ON?

719
00:49:35,706 --> 00:49:39,209
MAYBE.
THERE'S THIS GUY.

720
00:49:39,242 --> 00:49:41,578
HER LOVER?
YES.

721
00:49:41,611 --> 00:49:43,480
BUT HE DOESN'T
SEEM TO KNOW ANYTHING.

722
00:49:43,513 --> 00:49:47,117
GRIFFIN, HOW DO YOU KNOW WHEN
YOUR MATE IS HAVING AN AFFAIR?

723
00:49:48,218 --> 00:49:50,087
I'M SURE THERE ARE SIGNS.

724
00:49:50,120 --> 00:49:52,155
INTIMATE ONES, BUT I
WOULDN'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

725
00:49:52,189 --> 00:49:56,059
WHY ARE YOU ALWAYS
SO HARD ON ME?

726
00:49:56,093 --> 00:49:59,196
EVER SINCE I CAME HERE,
IT'S LIKE I CAN
DO NOTHING RIGHT.

727
00:49:59,229 --> 00:50:03,467
ELIZABETH, YOU HAVE
THE POTENTIAL TO FLY,
BUT YOU'RE STILL CRAWLING.

728
00:50:05,235 --> 00:50:07,204
AND THERE IS ANOTHER REASON

729
00:50:07,237 --> 00:50:09,706
WHY I HAD
TO KEEP MY DISTANCE.

730
00:50:09,740 --> 00:50:13,110
I KNOW WHY. IT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE A PROFESSIONAL,

731
00:50:13,143 --> 00:50:15,245
AND I'M NOTHING
BUT A SCANDALOUS FRESHMAN.

732
00:50:15,278 --> 00:50:17,414
BELIEVE ME, I GET IT.

733
00:50:17,447 --> 00:50:19,249
ELIZABETH, EVER SINCE
WE FIRST MET

734
00:50:19,282 --> 00:50:22,452
WHEN I WAS LECTURING
AT COLUMBIA UNIVERSITY
I SAW HOW MUCH ALIKE WE ARE.

735
00:50:22,486 --> 00:50:27,524
I'VE WATCHED YOU BLOSSOM
INTO THIS INCREDIBLY
AMAZING WOMAN.

736
00:50:27,557 --> 00:50:33,230
AND I'VE ALWAYS KNOWN
THAT YOU HAD IT IN YOU
TO BE AN INCREDIBLE JOURNALIST.

737
00:50:33,263 --> 00:50:36,366
YOU THINK I'M GOOD?
YES, I DO.

738
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:38,402
WHY DIDN'T YOU EVER TELL ME?

739
00:50:41,171 --> 00:50:44,341
WHAT I DIDN'T COUNT ON WAS--

740
00:50:46,410 --> 00:50:50,547
WAS FALLING IN LOVE WITH YOU.

741
00:50:50,580 --> 00:50:52,315
ELIZABETH,

742
00:50:52,349 --> 00:50:55,285
LET ME JUST SAY,

743
00:50:55,318 --> 00:50:57,120
I THINK WE WOULD
BE A GREAT TEAM.

744
00:50:57,154 --> 00:51:00,724
I THINK WE COULD HAVE
AN AMAZING LIFE TOGETHER.

745
00:51:02,459 --> 00:51:05,796
WOULD YOU CARE TO DISCUSS THIS
AT ANOTHER TIME?

746
00:51:15,605 --> 00:51:19,776
[ANN]
HE GIVES ME FLOWERS,
BEAUTIFUL FLOWERS.

747
00:51:19,810 --> 00:51:22,212
WHEN HE KISSES ME,
IT'S ELECTRIC.

748
00:51:22,245 --> 00:51:26,216
AND DID I MENTION TO YOU
THAT HE REALLY KNOWS HOW
TO SATISFY A WOMAN?

749
00:51:26,249 --> 00:51:27,918
[ELIZABETH]
YOU'RE SHAMELESS.

750
00:51:27,951 --> 00:51:30,253
[ANN LAUGHING]
PERHAPS. BUT I'M HAPPY.

751
00:51:30,287 --> 00:51:33,824
YOU DON'T KNOW HAPPINESS
UNTIL YOU'VE HAD
A LOVER LIKE BOB.

752
00:51:35,325 --> 00:51:36,693
[PHONE RINGING]

753
00:51:36,726 --> 00:51:38,161
HELLO?

754
00:51:38,195 --> 00:51:39,830
DO YOU LIKE THEM?

755
00:51:41,264 --> 00:51:45,202
YES. THEY'RE VERY BEAUTIFUL.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

756
00:51:45,235 --> 00:51:47,871
I DIDN'T MEAN
TO UPSET YOU EARLIER.

757
00:51:47,904 --> 00:51:50,440
[SIGHS]

758
00:51:50,474 --> 00:51:52,676
IT'S OKAY, IT'S JUST--

759
00:51:52,709 --> 00:51:54,244
WELL, YOU CAUGHT ME
OFF GUARD.

760
00:51:54,277 --> 00:51:58,248
LISTEN, I THINK I MIGHT
HAVE SOME GOOD NEWS FOR YOU.

761
00:51:58,281 --> 00:52:00,250
I FOUND ANN'S HOTEL RECEIPT.

762
00:52:00,283 --> 00:52:03,787
MAYBE IT'LL HELP.

763
00:52:03,820 --> 00:52:05,856
WHEN CAN I GET IT?

764
00:52:05,889 --> 00:52:08,859
OH, UM, HOW ABOUT
TOMORROW NIGHT?

765
00:52:08,892 --> 00:52:11,361
AFTER MY SHOW.

766
00:52:11,394 --> 00:52:12,162
REALLY?YEAH.

767
00:52:12,195 --> 00:52:15,599
YOU COULD, UH--
YOU COULD COME OVER.

768
00:52:15,632 --> 00:52:17,300
YOU HAVE THE ADDRESS, RIGHT?

769
00:52:17,334 --> 00:52:19,970
IT'S ON THE CARD
WITH THE FLOWERS.

770
00:52:20,003 --> 00:52:23,206
OKAY. I'LL BE THERE.

771
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:26,610
OKAY. GOOD.

772
00:52:26,643 --> 00:52:28,345
I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE YOU.

773
00:52:28,378 --> 00:52:30,213
WAIT A MINUTE, BOB?
YEAH?

774
00:52:30,247 --> 00:52:32,249
ONE MORE THING.

775
00:52:33,984 --> 00:52:36,319
WHERE WERE YOU
LAST WEDNESDAY?

776
00:52:38,488 --> 00:52:42,225
HMM. I WAS--
[CHUCKLES]
I WAS DOING MY PLAY.

777
00:52:42,259 --> 00:52:45,262
DID YOU SEE ANN
AFTERWARDS?

778
00:52:45,295 --> 00:52:48,765
NO, I WISH I DID.
LET ME SEE.

779
00:52:48,798 --> 00:52:53,336
I CAME HOME,
I FINISHED THIS BIO
I WAS READING ON OLIVIER.

780
00:52:53,370 --> 00:52:55,238
I, UH, MADE A POT OF COFFEE.

781
00:52:55,272 --> 00:52:57,574
MOCHA BEANS. UM--

782
00:52:57,607 --> 00:52:59,376
I SMOKED A CIGAR,

783
00:52:59,409 --> 00:53:02,812
BRUSHED MY TEETH,
HAD A PINT OF GREAT ICE CREAM.

784
00:53:02,846 --> 00:53:04,514
ALL RIGHT,
I GET THE PICTURE.

785
00:53:04,548 --> 00:53:06,416
[LAUGHING]

786
00:53:06,449 --> 00:53:08,585
WAIT, WHAT FLAVOR?

787
00:53:08,618 --> 00:53:11,988
OH, UH, PEANUT-BUTTER SWIRL.

788
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:13,590
MMM.

789
00:53:15,525 --> 00:53:19,829
I HOPE THIS WAS
PRE-TOOTH BRUSHING.

790
00:53:19,863 --> 00:53:22,365
[LAUGHING]

791
00:53:22,399 --> 00:53:24,434
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE WEIRD.

792
00:53:24,467 --> 00:53:27,370
YEAH. WAIT, I DIDN'T TELL YOU
ABOUT MY WHOLE HAIR PROCESS.

793
00:53:27,404 --> 00:53:30,340
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S ENOUGH.

794
00:53:30,373 --> 00:53:32,709
[LAUGHING]

795
00:53:32,742 --> 00:53:37,814
I'M, UM-- I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT EARLIER TODAY.

796
00:53:37,847 --> 00:53:39,950
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

797
00:53:39,983 --> 00:53:42,485
TOMORROW NIGHT.

798
00:53:54,831 --> 00:53:56,299
[CHUCKLING]

799
00:53:56,333 --> 00:53:57,667
HERE YOU GO.
THANKS.

800
00:53:57,701 --> 00:54:00,403
LET'S GRAB A COFFEE.

801
00:54:00,437 --> 00:54:02,439
CAN WE HAVE A COUPLE
OF ICE COFFEES, PLEASE?

802
00:54:02,472 --> 00:54:03,540
THANK YOU.

803
00:54:03,573 --> 00:54:05,308
NO PROBLEM, HERE YOU GO.

804
00:54:08,078 --> 00:54:10,880
HOW'S THE STORY
COMING ALONG?
GOOD.

805
00:54:10,914 --> 00:54:15,018
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I HAVE A DATE TONIGHT TO PICK UP
A PIECE OF THE MISSING PUZZLE.

806
00:54:15,051 --> 00:54:18,622
AND WHO HAS THAT PIECE?
FRIEND OF A FRIEND.

807
00:54:18,655 --> 00:54:21,424
DOES THIS FRIEND
PLAY A PART IN THE FANTASY?

808
00:54:21,458 --> 00:54:23,026
YOU COULD SAY THAT.

809
00:54:23,059 --> 00:54:26,696
BUT IT'S JUST
A FANTASY, RIGHT?
LAURIE, I'M JUST DOING MY JOB.

810
00:54:26,730 --> 00:54:28,365
I KNOW. I BELIEVE YOU.

811
00:54:28,398 --> 00:54:32,335
HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM THE DETECTIVE
IN NEW YORK ABOUT BOB?

812
00:54:32,369 --> 00:54:34,404
NOT YET.

813
00:54:34,437 --> 00:54:36,339
HE ALWAYS DELIVERS.

814
00:54:36,373 --> 00:54:38,308
[ELIZABETH]
GOD, I HOPE SO.

815
00:54:58,995 --> 00:55:01,498
[KNOCKING]
COME IN, IT'S OPEN.

816
00:55:03,066 --> 00:55:04,701
HI.

817
00:55:04,734 --> 00:55:06,469
HI.

818
00:55:06,503 --> 00:55:10,707
WELCOME TO MY BEAUTIFUL ABODE.

819
00:55:10,740 --> 00:55:12,375
WOW, IT'S GREAT.

820
00:55:12,409 --> 00:55:14,511
THANKS.
CONGRATULATIONS.

821
00:55:14,544 --> 00:55:17,514
I READ YOUR REVIEWS,
THEY'RE REALLY GREAT.

822
00:55:17,547 --> 00:55:20,517
YEAH. YEAH,
LOOKS LIKE I'M, UH,

823
00:55:20,550 --> 00:55:22,719
FINALLY STARTING TO GET
THE RECOGNITION I DESERVE.

824
00:55:22,752 --> 00:55:25,822
"KISS OR KILL."

825
00:55:25,855 --> 00:55:27,524
[LAUGHING]

826
00:55:27,557 --> 00:55:31,027
I LIKE THAT.
ME TOO. SIT DOWN.

827
00:55:31,061 --> 00:55:33,730
MAKE YOURSELF
COMFORTABLE. RELAX.
TAKE YOUR COAT OFF.

828
00:55:35,832 --> 00:55:37,801
THANKS.

829
00:55:39,703 --> 00:55:42,505
I THINK WE SHOULD
HAVE A DRINK.

830
00:55:44,541 --> 00:55:47,444
HERE'S TO BEING ABSOLUTELY

831
00:55:47,477 --> 00:55:49,546
TOTALLY,

832
00:55:49,579 --> 00:55:52,682
100% ALIVE--

833
00:55:52,716 --> 00:55:54,551
TRULY ALIVE.

834
00:55:54,584 --> 00:55:56,586
[LAUGHS]

835
00:55:57,754 --> 00:56:00,857
I HAVE A FEELING
YOU KNOW A LOT ABOUT THAT.

836
00:56:00,890 --> 00:56:02,559
I DO.

837
00:56:06,529 --> 00:56:08,865
OH, MY GOD, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU HAVE THAT PICTURE.

838
00:56:08,898 --> 00:56:11,067
I HAVE THE SAME
EXACT ONE IN MY HOUSE.

839
00:56:11,101 --> 00:56:12,635
REALLY? I'VE HAD THAT
SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.

840
00:56:12,669 --> 00:56:13,837
ME, TOO.
NO WAY.

841
00:56:13,870 --> 00:56:16,573
WHEN I FIRST SAW IT,
I WAS TRULY AMAZED.

842
00:56:22,078 --> 00:56:23,546
YOU BOX, TOO?

843
00:56:23,580 --> 00:56:25,715
YES, I DO.

844
00:56:27,584 --> 00:56:29,519
SO DO I.

845
00:56:29,552 --> 00:56:30,754
YOU DO?

846
00:56:30,787 --> 00:56:33,590
A LITTLE BIT.

847
00:56:33,623 --> 00:56:35,759
LET ME GET THAT
RECEIPT FOR YOU.
OKAY.

848
00:56:43,199 --> 00:56:44,901
HERE.

849
00:56:44,934 --> 00:56:46,469
THANK YOU.

850
00:56:52,642 --> 00:56:53,843
HERE, HERE, HERE.

851
00:56:55,545 --> 00:56:56,846
TASTE THAT.

852
00:57:08,057 --> 00:57:09,726
I GOTTA GO.

853
00:57:11,060 --> 00:57:14,631
[MOANING]
WHERE YOU GONNA GO?

854
00:57:50,333 --> 00:57:51,768
OH.

855
00:58:11,688 --> 00:58:14,190
[MOANING]

856
00:58:22,799 --> 00:58:25,134
[MOANING]

857
01:00:25,922 --> 01:00:28,024
SON OF A BITCH.

858
01:00:30,026 --> 01:00:31,427
WHAT THE HELL--

859
01:00:33,096 --> 01:00:35,798
THINK YOU'RE GONNA NAIL ME?
NO FUCKING WAY.

860
01:00:35,832 --> 01:00:37,667
NO FUCKING WAY.

861
01:00:41,838 --> 01:00:42,705
[SIGHING]

862
01:00:45,408 --> 01:00:47,677
[DOOR OPENING, CLOSING]

863
01:00:57,920 --> 01:00:59,355
SHIT.

864
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:04,994
[TOILET FLUSHING]

865
01:01:08,264 --> 01:01:09,999
[WHISPERING]
WHERE IS IT?

866
01:01:21,077 --> 01:01:22,812
"JENNIFER."

867
01:01:23,813 --> 01:01:25,815
[MOUTHING]

868
01:01:27,984 --> 01:01:30,086
YOU WANT SOME COFFEE?

869
01:01:31,087 --> 01:01:33,890
YEAH. THANKS.
[SPITTING]

870
01:01:33,923 --> 01:01:35,391
MORNING.

871
01:01:48,871 --> 01:01:50,273
[MACHINE BEEPS]

872
01:01:50,306 --> 01:01:53,076
[ERIC]
HEY, IT'S ME. YOU THERE?

873
01:01:53,109 --> 01:01:54,911
LIZZY?

874
01:01:54,944 --> 01:01:56,345
I MISS YOU.

875
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:57,780
[BEEPS]

876
01:01:57,814 --> 01:01:59,916
[ERIC]
BABY, WHERE ARE YA?

877
01:01:59,949 --> 01:02:03,319
I HOPE EVERYTHING'S OKAY.
LOOK, THINGS
ARE GOING GREAT UP HERE.

878
01:02:03,352 --> 01:02:06,789
I WANT TO APOLOGIZE.
I'M SORRY. I LOVE YOU.
CALL ME AT THE HOTEL.

879
01:02:06,823 --> 01:02:08,825
[BEEPS]

880
01:02:08,858 --> 01:02:11,894
[GRIFFIN]
WHERE'S MY STORY, ELIZABETH?
YOUR TIME'S UP.

881
01:02:11,928 --> 01:02:14,564
[BEEPS]
[WHISPERS]
WHAT IF I CAN'T DO THIS?

882
01:02:14,597 --> 01:02:16,332
[MAN]
YEAH, THIS IS
DETECTIVE JAMES MARTIN.

883
01:02:16,365 --> 01:02:18,201
I GOT THAT INFORMATION
YOU REQUESTED.

884
01:02:18,234 --> 01:02:20,803
I'M GONNA FAX YOU
THE RAP SHEET ON THIS GUY.

885
01:02:20,837 --> 01:02:23,840
HE'S A SEASONED CRIMINAL WITH
SEVERAL FELONIES ON HIS RECORD.

886
01:02:23,873 --> 01:02:25,875
YOU SHOULD BE REAL CAREFUL
AROUND HIM.

887
01:02:25,908 --> 01:02:27,877
[BEEPS]

888
01:02:37,887 --> 01:02:39,288
[GASPS]

889
01:02:42,992 --> 01:02:44,694
[EXHALES]

890
01:02:48,564 --> 01:02:50,967
ERIC, WHERE ARE YOU?

891
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:53,035
[CRYING]
WHERE ARE YOU?

892
01:02:56,873 --> 01:02:58,107
[WOMAN]
SAN FRANCISCO HILTON.

893
01:02:58,141 --> 01:02:59,542
ERIC BARTON, PLEASE.

894
01:02:59,575 --> 01:03:01,177
UH, HE CHECKED OUT
THIS MORNING.

895
01:03:01,210 --> 01:03:03,946
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
HE CHECKED OUT?
ARE YOU SURE?

896
01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:07,917
YES, POSITIVE.
YEAH, OKAY. THANK YOU.

897
01:03:08,918 --> 01:03:10,419
HE CHECKED OUT.

898
01:03:12,655 --> 01:03:15,591
ERIC, WHERE ARE YOU
WHEN I NEED YOU?

899
01:03:15,625 --> 01:03:17,960
WHERE THE FUCK ARE YOU?

900
01:03:20,897 --> 01:03:23,199
FUCKING LIES!

901
01:03:31,908 --> 01:03:33,943
[SOBBING]

902
01:03:45,121 --> 01:03:46,956
HI.
HEY.

903
01:03:46,989 --> 01:03:49,091
CAN YOU HELP ME? SURE.

904
01:03:49,125 --> 01:03:52,028
A FRIEND OF MINE MAY HAVE
PURCHASED SOMETHING HERE.

905
01:03:52,061 --> 01:03:53,930
CAN YOU MAKE
ANY SENSE OF THIS?

906
01:03:53,963 --> 01:03:57,033
CAN MAKE OUT A FIRST NAME--
JENNIFER. BUT THAT'S ABOUT IT.

907
01:03:57,066 --> 01:03:59,001
LAST NAME IS TOO SMUDGED.
[SIGHS]

908
01:03:59,035 --> 01:04:01,971
WELL, IS THERE ANY OTHER SOURCE
WHERE IT MIGHT BE?

909
01:04:02,004 --> 01:04:03,940
NOT ON A FIRST-TIME BUYER.

910
01:04:03,973 --> 01:04:07,510
NICE-LOOKING LADY, THOUGH.
GREAT LEGS.

911
01:04:07,543 --> 01:04:09,545
CAN YOU TELL
WHAT SHE BOUGHT?

912
01:04:09,579 --> 01:04:14,584
SONY EIGHT MILLIMETER VIDEO
CAMERA WITH AN AUTOMATIC TIMER.

913
01:04:14,617 --> 01:04:16,552
SHE WANTED THAT.
FOR THE CAMERA?

914
01:04:16,586 --> 01:04:21,224
SURE. SECURITY, SURVEILLANCE,
KINKY STUFF IN THE BEDROOM.
[CHUCKLES]

915
01:04:21,257 --> 01:04:24,160
NO, JUST KIDDING. SHE DIDN'T
SEEM THE TYPE. HE DID.

916
01:04:24,193 --> 01:04:25,962
HE?
YEAH, THE GUY WITH HER.

917
01:04:25,995 --> 01:04:29,065
TALL, DARK,
KIND OF ITALIAN.

918
01:04:29,098 --> 01:04:31,234
PASSING HIMSELF OFF
AS AN ACTOR.

919
01:04:31,267 --> 01:04:34,303
GREAT EXCUSE NOT TO WORK
IF YOU ASK ME.

920
01:04:34,337 --> 01:04:36,005
FUNNY, I JUST CALLED.

921
01:04:36,038 --> 01:04:38,140
HIS ORDER IS READY.
WHAT ORDER?

922
01:04:38,174 --> 01:04:41,477
MADE SOME DUPES FOR HIM,
COPIES OF A VIDEO.

923
01:04:41,510 --> 01:04:45,114
IT WAS A RUSH ORDER, I GUESS.
SOMETHING IMPORTANT.

924
01:04:45,147 --> 01:04:47,683
I'D GET IT FOR YOU,
BUT IT'S NOT HERE.

925
01:04:47,717 --> 01:04:51,053
WE FARMED IT OUT.
HE'S PICKING IT UP
DIRECTLY FROM THE LAB DOWNTOWN.

926
01:04:56,259 --> 01:04:59,328
TELL THEM I SENT YOU.

927
01:04:59,362 --> 01:05:02,064
THANK YOU.
HEY, COME BACK ANY TIME!

928
01:05:02,098 --> 01:05:03,966
I GET YOU A DEAL ON A VIDEO.

929
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:06,702
[BELL RINGS]
MMM!

930
01:05:06,736 --> 01:05:08,070
YEAH.

931
01:05:11,340 --> 01:05:15,144
[GRIFFIN] HONESTLY, I DON'T
SEE ONE DECENT PHOTOGRAPH
OF THE WHOLE BUNCH.

932
01:05:15,177 --> 01:05:17,980
WELL, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT--

933
01:05:18,014 --> 01:05:21,150
PLEASE, JUST ONE MORE DAY.
I'M ONTO SOMETHING, I SWEAR.

934
01:05:21,183 --> 01:05:22,985
HOLD ON A SECOND.

935
01:05:23,019 --> 01:05:24,687
ELIZABETH, I NEED REAL PROOF.

936
01:05:24,720 --> 01:05:26,322
I'M GETTING IT.

937
01:05:28,124 --> 01:05:31,460
LEAVE IT HERE. I'LL GIVE IT
A READ. MEET ME ACROSS
THE STREET AT 5:30

938
01:05:31,494 --> 01:05:33,996
AND LEAVE
YOUR CELL NUMBER.

939
01:05:34,030 --> 01:05:35,998
NO, NOT YOU.

940
01:05:36,032 --> 01:05:39,001
WELL, HONESTLY, JUST THE THOUGHT
OF LOOKING AT THEM AGAIN
MAKES ME NAUSEOUS.

941
01:05:39,035 --> 01:05:41,704
FORGET ABOUT IT.
I'M PULLING YOU OFF THE PROJECT.

942
01:06:27,083 --> 01:06:29,251
[LINE RINGING]

943
01:06:29,285 --> 01:06:30,453
[MACHINE BEEPS]

944
01:06:30,486 --> 01:06:32,822
GRIFF, ELIZABETH.
I'M ON TO SOMETHING.

945
01:06:32,855 --> 01:06:36,692
335 BRILL. I'M GONNA BE LATE
FOR OUR 5:30, BUT I'LL BE THERE.

946
01:06:42,298 --> 01:06:45,101
GOTTA HAVE THE GUTS
TO KNOW YOUR ENDING, BETH.

947
01:06:45,134 --> 01:06:46,402
OKAY.

948
01:07:26,142 --> 01:07:27,276
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

949
01:07:27,309 --> 01:07:30,279
[BOB'S VOICE]
SHE WAS AN ABSOLUTE LEGEND.

950
01:07:30,312 --> 01:07:31,814
[BOB LAUGHING]

951
01:07:31,847 --> 01:07:35,284
I THINK THAT THIS
CHANGES EVERYTHING.

952
01:07:35,317 --> 01:07:36,819
NO WAY.

953
01:07:36,852 --> 01:07:39,588
HEY, I FULFILLED MY END
OF THE DEAL, MAN!

954
01:07:39,622 --> 01:07:44,126
YOU CAN'T JUST DECIDE THAT NOW!
I'M NOT GONNA LET YOU DO THIS!

955
01:07:46,462 --> 01:07:49,265
HEY, FUCK YOU, MAN!
WE HAD A DEAL.

956
01:07:49,298 --> 01:07:51,867
THE GIRL IS FINE.

957
01:07:53,436 --> 01:07:57,139
LISTEN, I'M WATCHING
THIS THING RIGHT NOW.
WELL, LISTEN TO ME.

958
01:07:57,173 --> 01:08:00,176
I'VE GOT THE ORIGINAL AND
I'VE GOT THE ONLY COPIES, OKAY?

959
01:08:00,209 --> 01:08:01,477
SO, WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

960
01:08:01,510 --> 01:08:04,780
LOOK, IF SHE BECOMES
A PROBLEM, I'LL TAKE
CARE OF HER PERSONALLY.

961
01:08:07,483 --> 01:08:09,452
UH, I'M GONNA CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK.

962
01:08:12,822 --> 01:08:14,657
[BOB]
HEY!

963
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:17,293
ELIZABETH!

964
01:08:17,326 --> 01:08:18,627
WAIT UP!

965
01:08:34,276 --> 01:08:35,311
[SCREAMS]

966
01:08:40,883 --> 01:08:42,418
[PANTING]

967
01:08:49,959 --> 01:08:51,494
[HITTING BUTTONS]

968
01:08:51,527 --> 01:08:53,762
[SCREAMS]
COME ON!

969
01:08:57,233 --> 01:08:58,367
COME ON.

970
01:08:58,400 --> 01:09:00,703
[PANTING]

971
01:09:14,250 --> 01:09:15,551
[PANTING]

972
01:09:22,591 --> 01:09:25,227
DAMN! FUCK!

973
01:09:26,562 --> 01:09:27,830
[SCREAMS]

974
01:09:27,863 --> 01:09:29,899
ELIZABETH, GOD,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

975
01:09:29,932 --> 01:09:30,966
MY STORY JUST GOT BIGGER.

976
01:09:31,000 --> 01:09:34,236
THE WOMAN I'VE BEEN
LOOKING FOR, I THINK SHE'S DEAD.

977
01:09:34,270 --> 01:09:37,506
DEAD? MY GOD,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

978
01:09:37,540 --> 01:09:39,942
I'LL CHECK IN LATER.

979
01:09:39,975 --> 01:09:44,280
NAILING THE ENDING
OF YOUR STORY DOES NOT MEAN
THE END OF YOU, ELIZABETH.

980
01:09:44,313 --> 01:09:46,482
DO YOU HAVE PROOF?
I'M THIS CLOSE.

981
01:09:52,288 --> 01:09:55,724
MY GOD, CHILD, WHAT HAVE YOU
GOTTEN YOURSELF INTO?

982
01:09:55,758 --> 01:09:58,861
[GRIFFIN]
LIZZY, HONEY, WHERE ARE YOU?

983
01:09:58,894 --> 01:10:00,563
LIZZY?

984
01:10:20,382 --> 01:10:21,684
IS HE AT THE THEATER YET?

985
01:10:21,717 --> 01:10:24,486
HE'S SCHEDULED TO GO ON TONIGHT,
BUT HE ISN'T HERE YET.

986
01:10:24,520 --> 01:10:26,355
DAMN IT, I'VE GOTTA
GET THAT TAPE.

987
01:10:26,388 --> 01:10:29,291
I KNOW THAT'S WHAT
ANN WAS TRYING TO SAY
ON MY ANSWERING MACHINE.

988
01:10:29,325 --> 01:10:33,629
HOW DO YOU KNOW HE HASN'T?
BECAUSE I SNUCK OVER TO HIS
PLACE AND SAW HIM WATCHING IT.

989
01:10:33,662 --> 01:10:37,399
I'VE GOTTA GET IN THERE,
GET IT AND GET OUT.
YOU'RE IN WAY OVER YOUR HEAD.

990
01:10:37,433 --> 01:10:41,470
YOU SHOULD BE CAREFUL.
I KNOW, BUT LIKE GRIFF SAYS,
NO GUTS, NO STORY.

991
01:10:41,503 --> 01:10:44,873
LAURIE, I NEED YOU
TO BUY ME SOME TIME.
IF HE SHOWS UP HERE,

992
01:10:44,907 --> 01:10:47,643
JUST MAKE SURE
HE DOESN'T LEAVE.

993
01:10:49,478 --> 01:10:51,347
BE CAREFUL.

994
01:11:29,718 --> 01:11:31,620
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

995
01:11:35,424 --> 01:11:37,359
[DOOR OPENING]

996
01:11:37,393 --> 01:11:38,994
[MAN]
OKAY, THANKS!
SEE YOU LATER.

997
01:11:49,471 --> 01:11:50,773
BOB?

998
01:11:54,510 --> 01:11:56,145
[MAN GASPS]

999
01:11:56,178 --> 01:11:58,447
[GASPING]

1000
01:11:58,480 --> 01:12:01,517
[GASPING]
THE DUDE.

1001
01:12:01,550 --> 01:12:02,685
I'M NOT--

1002
01:12:05,688 --> 01:12:07,623
[FOOTSTEPS CLIMBING STAIRS]

1003
01:12:11,894 --> 01:12:16,365
[MAN WHISTLING]

1004
01:12:35,617 --> 01:12:38,587
[PLASTIC RUSTLING]

1005
01:12:43,826 --> 01:12:45,694
[ZIPPER CLOSING]

1006
01:13:00,142 --> 01:13:04,146
[BODY BAG DRAGGING
ON FLOOR]

1007
01:13:13,589 --> 01:13:15,424
[GASPING]

1008
01:13:25,868 --> 01:13:28,504
[CAR DOOR OPENING]

1009
01:13:28,537 --> 01:13:30,939
[DOOR CLOSING]

1010
01:13:34,042 --> 01:13:35,477
ERIC?

1011
01:13:45,087 --> 01:13:49,658
[NO AUDIO]

1012
01:13:51,727 --> 01:13:53,462
OH, MY GOD.

1013
01:13:59,835 --> 01:14:02,638
[DIALING]

1014
01:14:02,671 --> 01:14:04,239
[LINE RINGING]

1015
01:14:04,273 --> 01:14:06,809
COME ON, PICK UP.
PICK UP.

1016
01:14:07,810 --> 01:14:09,578
GRIFF!

1017
01:14:09,611 --> 01:14:12,114
ELIZABETH?
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE
 WHAT I'VE JUST SEEN.

1018
01:14:12,147 --> 01:14:16,084
WHAT'S WRONG?
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
ELIZABETH, WHAT'S WRONG?

1019
01:14:16,118 --> 01:14:18,720
ELIZABETH?

1020
01:14:18,754 --> 01:14:20,189
[CAR DOOR CLOSING]
WHERE ARE YOU?

1021
01:14:20,222 --> 01:14:22,691
OH, SHIT.
HE'S STILL HERE.
ELIZABETH!

1022
01:14:22,724 --> 01:14:23,759
HE'S HERE!
WHO?

1023
01:14:23,792 --> 01:14:26,929
PICK ME UP AT THE MARKET
ON OCEAN. PLEASE HURRY.

1024
01:14:33,001 --> 01:14:35,571
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

1025
01:14:45,247 --> 01:14:48,250
[ENGINE NOT TURNING OVER]

1026
01:14:52,087 --> 01:14:55,190
[ENGINE STARTS]

1027
01:15:14,877 --> 01:15:17,246
DRIVE!

1028
01:15:17,279 --> 01:15:20,949
[PANTING]
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

1029
01:15:20,983 --> 01:15:24,253
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE
THIS VIDEO-- WHAT'S ON IT,
WHAT I SAW TONIGHT.

1030
01:15:24,286 --> 01:15:26,688
HAVE YOU SPOKEN
TO ANYONE ELSE ABOUT THIS?

1031
01:15:26,722 --> 01:15:28,724
NO, I MEAN, I HAVEN'T HAD TIME.
I JUST CAME FROM THERE.

1032
01:15:28,757 --> 01:15:30,626
WHERE?
BOB'S.

1033
01:15:30,659 --> 01:15:33,095
BOB?
BOB WAS MURDERED
TONIGHT BY--

1034
01:15:33,128 --> 01:15:37,733
OH, MY GOD. BY, I THINK,
ERIC, BUT I DON'T KNOW.
IT JUST HAPPENED SO FAST.

1035
01:15:37,766 --> 01:15:39,268
MURDERED?

1036
01:15:39,301 --> 01:15:44,940
WELL, JUST RELAX, ELIZABETH.
I HAVE TO TAKE YOU SOMEWHERE
WHERE YOU'LL BE SAFE.

1037
01:15:44,973 --> 01:15:46,675
[GASPS]

1038
01:15:52,214 --> 01:15:54,850
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
MM-HMM.

1039
01:15:54,883 --> 01:15:56,618
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

1040
01:15:58,086 --> 01:16:00,589
I JUST HAVE TO MAKE
A LITTLE DETOUR.
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

1041
01:16:05,327 --> 01:16:08,764
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING ME?

1042
01:16:08,797 --> 01:16:11,133
I HAVE A LITTLE SURPRISE
FOR YOU, ELIZABETH.

1043
01:16:11,166 --> 01:16:12,901
[CHUCKLES]

1044
01:16:12,935 --> 01:16:17,372
DID I EVER TELL YOU
THAT I HATE SURPRISES?

1045
01:16:17,406 --> 01:16:18,874
[GASPING]

1046
01:16:26,982 --> 01:16:31,186
YOU CAN RUN, BUT YOU
SURELY CANNOT HIDE.

1047
01:16:31,219 --> 01:16:35,757
WHAT IS DESTINED
TO BE, SHALL BE.

1048
01:16:47,469 --> 01:16:48,704
[GRIFFIN]
PLEASE, MY LOVE.

1049
01:16:48,737 --> 01:16:51,239
[ELIZABETH]
WHAT IS IT?

1050
01:16:51,273 --> 01:16:53,075
[GRIFFIN]
IT'S FOR YOU.

1051
01:16:53,108 --> 01:16:54,977
[ELIZABETH]
I CAN'T.
OH, I THINK YOU CAN.

1052
01:16:55,010 --> 01:16:56,778
I THINK WE CAN.

1053
01:16:56,812 --> 01:16:58,814
CAN WHAT?

1054
01:16:58,847 --> 01:17:00,415
CAN DO WHATEVER WE WANT.

1055
01:17:00,449 --> 01:17:02,250
WHATEVER YOU WANT, ELIZABETH.

1056
01:17:02,284 --> 01:17:03,852
WE THINK WE KNOW LIFE.

1057
01:17:03,885 --> 01:17:06,388
WE THINK WE KNOW PEOPLE,
BUT WE DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

1058
01:17:06,421 --> 01:17:09,224
THE ONLY THING I AM CERTAIN OF
IS MY LOVING YOU.

1059
01:17:09,257 --> 01:17:12,227
I NEVER REALIZED I WAS CAPABLE
OF SO MUCH LOVE.

1060
01:17:12,260 --> 01:17:15,230
NOR OF DOING WHAT
I HAVE UNFORTUNATELY DONE,

1061
01:17:15,263 --> 01:17:17,265
WHICH CIRCUMSTANCES
HAVE FORCED ME TO DO.

1062
01:17:21,036 --> 01:17:24,773
ANN WAS AN EXCEPTIONALLY GIFTED
WOMAN AT MAKING PEOPLE BELIEVE

1063
01:17:24,806 --> 01:17:26,241
WHAT SHE WANTED
THEM TO BELIEVE.

1064
01:17:26,274 --> 01:17:29,244
EVERYONE THOUGHT
SHE WAS SUCH A DEVOTED WIFE.

1065
01:17:29,277 --> 01:17:32,014
WIFE?
OH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT THAT, ELIZABETH.

1066
01:17:32,047 --> 01:17:36,885
THE HATE IN OUR MARRIAGE STEMMED
FROM SOMETHING MORE SUBSTANTIAL
THAN MERE INFIDELITY.

1067
01:17:36,918 --> 01:17:39,121
SHE WANTED TO DESTROY ME,
DESTROY ALL MY DREAMS,

1068
01:17:39,154 --> 01:17:42,724
WHEN SHE REALIZED I WAS
NO LONGER IN LOVE WITH HER.

1069
01:17:42,758 --> 01:17:45,193
AND SHE WOULD HAVE
TAKEN EVERYTHING FROM ME.

1070
01:17:45,227 --> 01:17:49,031
SHE WAS AS MANIPULATING
AND COLD-BLOODED AS THEY COME.

1071
01:17:49,064 --> 01:17:52,200
SHE WAS PEERLESS IN THAT.
BUT LET'S NOT DWELL
ON THE MORBID.

1072
01:17:52,234 --> 01:17:55,804
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO HAVE SOME STRAWBERRIES?

1073
01:17:57,773 --> 01:17:58,840
PLEASE.

1074
01:18:00,776 --> 01:18:03,812
OUR LIFE TOGETHER WILL BE RATHER
EXTRAORDINARY FROM NOW ON.

1075
01:18:03,845 --> 01:18:07,082
TOGETHER WE WILL CONQUER
THE LITERARY WORLD.

1076
01:18:07,115 --> 01:18:10,852
WE'LL START AT A FIVE-YEAR
CONTRACT WITH THE MAGAZINE

1077
01:18:10,886 --> 01:18:13,055
STARTING AT
A SIX-FIGURE LEVEL.

1078
01:18:13,088 --> 01:18:15,057
CAR-- YOUR CHOICE OF COURSE.

1079
01:18:15,090 --> 01:18:18,994
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO HAVE A HOUSE IN MALIBU
AND A PENTHOUSE IN NEW YORK CITY

1080
01:18:19,027 --> 01:18:21,029
AND A TABLE OF YOUR OWN
AT ELAINE'S?

1081
01:18:21,063 --> 01:18:26,501
WE'LL GO TO ALL THE BEST PLACES.
YOU AND I WILL TRAVEL
THE WORLD TOGETHER. RIGHT?

1082
01:18:26,535 --> 01:18:30,739
ANYTHING YOUR HEART DESIRES,
YOU WILL HAVE.

1083
01:18:32,874 --> 01:18:35,077
HAVE YOU FORGOTTEN
THAT I HAVE A HUSBAND?

1084
01:18:35,110 --> 01:18:38,013
OH, YES, A HUSBAND THAT
STARTED THIS WHOLE DIRTY THING.

1085
01:18:38,046 --> 01:18:40,248
THE HUSBAND THAT CHEATED,
THE HUSBAND THAT LIED,

1086
01:18:40,282 --> 01:18:42,918
THE HUSBAND THAT DIDN'T
BELIEVE IN YOUR DREAMS,

1087
01:18:42,951 --> 01:18:46,521
JUST CARED ABOUT YOUR
PAYCHECK, DIDN'T GIVE A DAMN
ABOUT YOU AND YOUR LIFE.

1088
01:18:47,823 --> 01:18:52,928
YES, YOUR HUSBAND.
I'VE BEEN CONSIDERING THIS.

1089
01:18:58,300 --> 01:19:00,502
YOUR PRECIOUS HUSBAND.

1090
01:19:10,011 --> 01:19:12,547
HOW WILL YOU EXPLAIN ANN?

1091
01:19:13,615 --> 01:19:15,851
APPARENTLY,
ANN AND HER LOVER

1092
01:19:15,884 --> 01:19:19,855
ARE ON AN EXTENDED VACATION
IN BARBADOS.

1093
01:19:19,888 --> 01:19:22,858
PROBABLY WILL NOT BE RETURNING,
AND THAT OF COURSE
WILL DEVASTATE ME,

1094
01:19:22,891 --> 01:19:26,428
BUT I WILL CARRY ON.

1095
01:19:26,461 --> 01:19:28,263
WHAT ABOUT BOB?

1096
01:19:28,296 --> 01:19:31,199
SOMETIMES A MAN'S CHECKERED PAST
CATCHES UP WITH HIM

1097
01:19:31,233 --> 01:19:32,934
WHICH REQUIRES
A HASTY DEPARTURE,

1098
01:19:32,968 --> 01:19:37,139
USUALLY TO A FARAWAY,
FOREIGN COUNTRY.

1099
01:19:38,440 --> 01:19:40,909
YOU CERTAINLY
HAVE THOUGHT OF EVERYTHING.

1100
01:19:40,942 --> 01:19:42,177
YES, I HAVE.

1101
01:19:43,545 --> 01:19:46,948
LET'S SAY I'VE EDITED IT DOWN
TO A WORKABLE PIECE.

1102
01:19:46,982 --> 01:19:48,250
[LAUGHING]

1103
01:19:50,552 --> 01:19:53,388
BUT THE BOTTOM LINE,
ELIZABETH, IS I LOVE YOU.

1104
01:19:53,421 --> 01:19:55,991
I KNOW THE LIFESTYLE
THAT YOU WANT.

1105
01:19:56,024 --> 01:19:58,160
AND I CAN GIVE YOU
EVERYTHING YOU WANT.

1106
01:19:58,193 --> 01:20:02,597
THERE IS, HOWEVER,
ONE THING I MUST INSIST UPON.

1107
01:20:02,631 --> 01:20:04,599
WE TAKE CARE OF ERIC.

1108
01:20:04,633 --> 01:20:07,869
TAKE CARE OF?
WE'LL DO IT TOGETHER.

1109
01:20:07,903 --> 01:20:10,939
THAT WILL SEAL
OUR BOND OF LOVE.

1110
01:20:10,972 --> 01:20:12,474
[LOUD KNOCKING]
[GASPING]

1111
01:20:14,442 --> 01:20:17,179
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

1112
01:20:17,212 --> 01:20:21,016
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND,
I'VE INVITED A FRIEND OF YOURS.

1113
01:20:21,049 --> 01:20:23,051
ERIC.

1114
01:20:23,084 --> 01:20:27,122
THANK YOU
FOR JOINING US. PLEASE.

1115
01:20:27,155 --> 01:20:29,658
I'M SURE YOU KNOW
THE YOUNG LADY,
OUR NEW STAFF JOURNALIST.

1116
01:20:29,691 --> 01:20:32,227
PLEASE HAVE A SEAT.

1117
01:20:34,362 --> 01:20:37,065
SO YOU ACTUALLY MADE
THE BIG TIME? YOU'RE
THE NEW STAFF WRITER?

1118
01:20:37,098 --> 01:20:41,002
OH, YES.
ELIZABETH IS DESTINED
FOR BIG THINGS, INDEED.

1119
01:20:42,604 --> 01:20:44,673
CONGRATULATIONS, HONEY.

1120
01:20:44,706 --> 01:20:47,475
YES. I WAS JUST TELLING
ELIZABETH ABOUT THE APARTMENT.

1121
01:20:47,509 --> 01:20:51,112
FASCINATING STORY OF HOW
I CAME ABOUT FINDING THIS PLACE.

1122
01:20:51,146 --> 01:20:53,982
I THOUGHT THIS PLACE
WAS ANN'S.

1123
01:20:54,015 --> 01:20:57,385
SO DID ANN. LITTLE DID SHE KNOW
SHE WAS SUBLETTING FROM ME.

1124
01:20:57,419 --> 01:21:01,022
ERIC, I BELIEVE YOU KNOW
MY WIFE, ANN, DO YOU NOT?

1125
01:21:01,056 --> 01:21:04,659
UH, POSSIBLY.

1126
01:21:04,693 --> 01:21:07,028
HMM, POSSIBLY.

1127
01:21:07,062 --> 01:21:08,630
FUNNY.

1128
01:21:08,663 --> 01:21:13,335
I THOUGHT FOR SURE YOU AND
MY WIFE WERE HAVING AN AFFAIR.

1129
01:21:13,368 --> 01:21:14,803
[SCOFFS]

1130
01:21:14,836 --> 01:21:18,039
ALL RIGHT. LIZZY,
THIS GUY'S OUT OF HIS MIND.
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

1131
01:21:18,073 --> 01:21:19,941
[GRUNTS]

1132
01:21:24,646 --> 01:21:27,015
NOW, DOES THAT HELP
REFRESH YOUR MEMORY?

1133
01:21:27,048 --> 01:21:28,950
[COCKS GUN]

1134
01:21:29,985 --> 01:21:32,254
ONE OF THOSE LONG,
LINGERING AFTERNOONS

1135
01:21:32,287 --> 01:21:34,656
UP THERE IN MY HOTEL
WITH MY WIFE.

1136
01:21:34,689 --> 01:21:38,560
OR DO YOU NEED TO SIT DOWN,
COLLECT YOUR THOUGHTS?

1137
01:21:42,597 --> 01:21:46,201
PUT YOUR PATHETIC ASS
IN THIS CHAIR.

1138
01:21:46,234 --> 01:21:48,336
WHAT IS THIS BULLSHIT?

1139
01:21:48,370 --> 01:21:51,039
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE FUCK
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT!

1140
01:21:51,072 --> 01:21:52,340
SEE? HE DOESN'T
KNOW ANYTHING.

1141
01:21:55,143 --> 01:21:56,578
HE DOESN'T?

1142
01:21:59,581 --> 01:22:02,050
EXHIBIT "A",
ANN'S DIARY.

1143
01:22:02,083 --> 01:22:05,553
LET ME READ A FEW PASSAGES.

1144
01:22:05,587 --> 01:22:09,090
"AUGUST 19TH,"
JUST SEVERAL MONTHS AGO,

1145
01:22:09,124 --> 01:22:15,063
"ERIC MADE SUCH A FUNNY JOKE
TODAY ABOUT THAT NITWIT WIFE
OF HIS, THE WRITER.

1146
01:22:15,096 --> 01:22:21,036
"THE JOKE WAS, 'WAS SHE MORE
INEXPERIENCED AT MAKING LOVE
OR WRITING?'

1147
01:22:21,069 --> 01:22:23,104
GOD, DID WE LAUGH."

1148
01:22:23,138 --> 01:22:24,372
YOU'RE LYING.
I NEVER SAID THAT!

1149
01:22:24,406 --> 01:22:26,741
IT'S ALL RIGHT HERE.
NO!

1150
01:22:26,775 --> 01:22:28,443
NO! YOU'RE LYING!
HE'S LYING!

1151
01:22:28,476 --> 01:22:29,678
IS THIS LYING?

1152
01:22:33,081 --> 01:22:34,549
ALL RIGHT.

1153
01:22:36,685 --> 01:22:39,154
IT HAPPENED BEFORE
WE MET, I SWEAR.

1154
01:22:39,187 --> 01:22:42,290
IS THAT BEING
A DEVOTED HUSBAND, ERIC?

1155
01:22:42,324 --> 01:22:44,359
I THINK IT'S DISGUSTING.

1156
01:22:44,392 --> 01:22:46,394
MAKING FUN OF YOUR
LOVELY WIFE'S DREAMS.

1157
01:22:46,428 --> 01:22:51,199
I KNEW IT.
I KNEW IT ALL ALONG.

1158
01:22:53,168 --> 01:22:56,504
ALL RIGHT, I HAD JUST
ABOUT ENOUGH OUT OF YOU,

1159
01:22:56,538 --> 01:22:58,206
YOU FUCKING PSYCHO!

1160
01:22:58,239 --> 01:23:01,543
[GUNSHOT]
GODDAMN!

1161
01:23:01,576 --> 01:23:03,345
[GROANING]

1162
01:23:06,314 --> 01:23:08,616
WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH THIS MAN?

1163
01:23:08,650 --> 01:23:12,354
WHY DO PEOPLE NOT BELIEVE
WHEN SOMEONE HAS A GUN
THEY WILL USE IT?

1164
01:23:12,387 --> 01:23:16,491
I HAVE YOUR WIFE AND A GUN
AND I WILL USE THE GUN AGAIN.

1165
01:23:18,526 --> 01:23:19,594
[GRUNTS]

1166
01:23:19,627 --> 01:23:21,262
[GROANING]

1167
01:23:21,296 --> 01:23:23,064
YOU OKAY?

1168
01:23:24,866 --> 01:23:26,468
[ERIC]
GET THE GUN!
GET THE GUN!

1169
01:23:33,808 --> 01:23:35,176
[GUNSHOT]

1170
01:23:39,180 --> 01:23:40,515
[MOANS]

1171
01:23:43,451 --> 01:23:45,220
HONEY! HONEY, YOU OKAY?

1172
01:23:45,253 --> 01:23:50,258
OH, GOD. OH, FUCK.

1173
01:23:50,291 --> 01:23:52,527
[SIRENS WAILING]

1174
01:23:58,266 --> 01:23:59,334
COME ON.

1175
01:24:02,570 --> 01:24:05,240
[ERIC]
IS HE DEAD?

1176
01:24:20,588 --> 01:24:24,359
[ELIZABETH]
I'M A WRITER NOW--
A SUCCESSFUL, SINGLE WRITER.

1177
01:24:24,392 --> 01:24:26,628
ERIC AND I TRIED
TO WORK IT OUT,

1178
01:24:26,661 --> 01:24:29,264
BUT IT WAS OBVIOUS THERE
WAS NOTHING LEFT TO WORK OUT.

1179
01:24:29,297 --> 01:24:32,434
OF COURSE,
GRIFF WASN'T DEAD.
[APPLAUSE]

1180
01:24:32,467 --> 01:24:35,403
TWO WEEKS AGO,
I HEARD THAT HE'D ESCAPED
FROM THE SANITARIUM.

1181
01:24:35,437 --> 01:24:38,606
THEY TOLD ME THAT HE SAID
THAT HE LIVED ONLY FOR ME.

1182
01:24:38,640 --> 01:24:40,875
AND IT'S FUNNY BECAUSE
I ALMOST ENVY THAT.

1183
01:24:40,909 --> 01:24:43,211
I WISH I FELT
THAT WAY ABOUT SOMEONE.

1184
01:24:43,244 --> 01:24:46,915
WHO KNOWS?
MAYBE SOMEDAY, I WILL.

1185
01:24:46,948 --> 01:24:48,516
GREAT BOOK.

1186
01:24:48,550 --> 01:24:50,118
THANK YOU.

1187
01:24:57,225 --> 01:24:58,593
THANKS FOR COMING.

1188
01:24:58,626 --> 01:25:00,829
AND YES, I AM
WRITING ANOTHER ONE.

1189
01:25:02,363 --> 01:25:05,200
THIS IS EXCITING.
THE TURNOUT IS SO GREAT.

1190
01:25:05,233 --> 01:25:07,535
I KNOW.
I'M SO PROUD OF YOU, LIZZY.

1191
01:25:07,569 --> 01:25:09,938
I'M GONNA GET YOU
SOME WATER.
OKAY.

1192
01:25:09,971 --> 01:25:11,806
CONGRATULATIONS, ELIZABETH.

1193
01:25:11,840 --> 01:25:15,376
YOU'VE BEEN ABLE TO SATISFY
A LOT OF PEOPLE'S FANTASY.

1194
01:25:16,845 --> 01:25:18,246
HOW'S THAT?

1195
01:25:18,279 --> 01:25:19,848
YOU SHOT THE BOSS.

1196
01:25:19,881 --> 01:25:20,882
OH.

1197
01:25:22,183 --> 01:25:26,421
I'D LOVE TO TAKE YOU TO DINNER.
I'M IN TOWN FOR A COUPLE DAYS.

1198
01:25:26,454 --> 01:25:30,191
I DON'T THINK SO.
UM, THIS PRESS TOUR,
IT'S KILLING ME.

1199
01:25:32,293 --> 01:25:34,229
BUT THANKS FOR THE OFFER.

1200
01:25:34,262 --> 01:25:36,331
RIGHT.

1201
01:25:38,233 --> 01:25:40,902
[GIGGLING]
NOW THAT IS
ONE GOOD-LOOKING MAN.

1202
01:25:40,935 --> 01:25:43,238
WHY DIDN'T YOU ACCEPT?

1203
01:25:43,271 --> 01:25:46,741
LAURIE, I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN ANYTHING CASUAL.

1204
01:25:46,774 --> 01:25:49,644
AND EVEN THE MOST
INNOCENT LITTLE AFFAIR

1205
01:25:49,677 --> 01:25:51,946
CAN END IN DISASTER.

1206
01:25:51,980 --> 01:25:54,082
I SUPPOSE YOU'RE RIGHT.

1207
01:25:58,353 --> 01:26:01,422
[GRIFFIN'S VOICE ECHOING]
YOU CAN RUN, BUT YOU
SURELY CANNOT HIDE.

1208
01:26:01,456 --> 01:26:02,690
[GASPS]

1209
01:26:04,592 --> 01:26:07,395
I'M SORRY.

1210
01:26:07,428 --> 01:26:09,364
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

1211
01:26:09,397 --> 01:26:13,334
YEAH, I'M FINE, UH--

1212
01:26:13,368 --> 01:26:16,204
CAN I SIGN THAT FOR YOU?
YES, PLEASE.

1213
01:26:22,443 --> 01:26:23,745
HERE YOU GO.

1214
01:26:23,778 --> 01:26:25,647
THANK YOU.

1215
01:26:32,954 --> 01:26:37,492
[GRIFFIN'S VOICE ECHOING]
WHAT IS DESTINED TO BE,
SHALL BE.

